WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.000
[suspenseful string music plays]

2
00:00:28.625 --> 00:00:30.164
[sighs]

3
00:00:30.166 --> 00:00:32.207
[fire crackling]

4
00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:40.625
[man] <i>Hard to know where to start.</i>

5
00:00:41.832 --> 00:00:45.249
<i>I guess to tell the story
of the Good Friday murder through my eyes.</i>

6
00:00:45.250 --> 00:00:46.957
<i>I got to start here.</i>

7
00:00:47.625 --> 00:00:51.749
<i>Nine months ago. when this asshole deacon
said something way out of line.</i>

8
00:00:51.750 --> 00:00:53.039
<i>and I did this.</i>

9
00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.500
- [imperceptible]
- [grunts]

10
00:00:56.040 --> 00:00:57.207
- [thuds]
- [priest gasps]

11
00:00:58.332 --> 00:00:59.957
Oh. shit.

12
00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:03.082
So. you're a fighter. then?

13
00:01:03.582 --> 00:01:05.706
Uh. no. Father. absolutely not.

14
00:01:05.707 --> 00:01:09.039
Well. we have a deacon who would say
otherwise if his jaw wasn't broken.

15
00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:11.750
In my previous life. yes. I was a boxer.

16
00:01:12.250 --> 00:01:14.831
and I lived on the streets.
I did some other things.

17
00:01:14.832 --> 00:01:18.707
We need fighters today.
but to fight the world.

18
00:01:19.457 --> 00:01:21.081
not ourselves.

19
00:01:21.082 --> 00:01:24.623
A priest is a shepherd.
The world is a wolf.

20
00:01:24.625 --> 00:01:25.832
No.

21
00:01:29.250 --> 00:01:33.623
[sighs softly] I... I don't believe that.
Father. respectfully.

22
00:01:33.625 --> 00:01:36.498
[hesitates] You start fighting wolves.
and before you know it.

23
00:01:36.500 --> 00:01:38.290
everyone you don't understand is a wolf.

24
00:01:39.332 --> 00:01:42.331
I still got that fighting instinct.
and I gave into it today.

25
00:01:42.332 --> 00:01:44.831
but Christ came to heal the world.
not fight it.

26
00:01:44.832 --> 00:01:46.206
I believe that.

27
00:01:46.207 --> 00:01:49.582
It's this. not this. you know?
[inhales deeply]

28
00:01:50.832 --> 00:01:52.665
I just want to be a good priest.

29
00:01:53.625 --> 00:01:56.914
Show broken people like me
the forgiveness and love of Christ.

30
00:01:56.915 --> 00:01:59.000
The world needs that so bad.

31
00:02:01.707 --> 00:02:04.582
You give me one more shot.
and I promise I'll do that.

32
00:02:05.082 --> 00:02:07.332
[church bell tolling in distance]

33
00:02:11.332 --> 00:02:14.000
- [church bell continues tolling]
- [vehicle horn honks]

34
00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:16.873
[tolling stops]

35
00:02:16.875 --> 00:02:18.125
Your Excellency.

36
00:02:18.832 --> 00:02:21.039
you stuck your neck out for me
so many times.

37
00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:23.623
- I let you down. and whatever the--
- All right.

38
00:02:23.625 --> 00:02:24.790
Listen...

39
00:02:25.290 --> 00:02:28.248
Deacon Clark is famously a dick.

40
00:02:28.250 --> 00:02:30.789
Nobody's actually that upset
that you clocked him.

41
00:02:30.790 --> 00:02:32.373
In fact. kind of the opposite.

42
00:02:32.375 --> 00:02:35.040
- But we do need to do something about it.
- [exhales]

43
00:02:36.040 --> 00:02:39.248
We're sending you
to a small parish in Chimney Rock.

44
00:02:39.250 --> 00:02:42.373
It's just one priest there now.

45
00:02:42.375 --> 00:02:43.581
[wind chime tinkling]

46
00:02:43.582 --> 00:02:44.998
Assistant pastor?

47
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:47.248
Yeah. well. curb your enthusiasm.

48
00:02:47.250 --> 00:02:48.165
What?

49
00:02:48.665 --> 00:02:53.414
[sighs] You're going
to Our Lady of Perpetual Fortitude.

50
00:02:53.415 --> 00:02:56.582
led by Monsignor Jefferson Wicks.
Have you heard of Jefferson Wicks?

51
00:02:57.457 --> 00:03:00.956
Okay. look. Wicks has his supporters here.
I'm not one of them.

52
00:03:00.957 --> 00:03:02.123
Between you and me.

53
00:03:02.125 --> 00:03:05.164
I think he's a few beads shy of
a full rosary and a real son of a bitch.

54
00:03:05.165 --> 00:03:06.081
[chuckles]

55
00:03:06.082 --> 00:03:10.832
But what's undeniable is that his flock
is shrinking and even calcifying.

56
00:03:11.790 --> 00:03:15.332
It could use some of what
you said in there. You understand?

57
00:03:15.957 --> 00:03:18.289
Not at all. but yes.

58
00:03:18.290 --> 00:03:20.456
Yes. yes. yes. yes. yes.

59
00:03:20.457 --> 00:03:23.414
- Spirit's got me. Let me at him.
- Hey. Hey. hey.

60
00:03:23.415 --> 00:03:27.040
This. not this. right? Mm?

61
00:03:31.165 --> 00:03:32.375
Good luck. kid.

62
00:03:33.040 --> 00:03:35.250
[intriguing music plays]

63
00:03:38.165 --> 00:03:40.790
[Jud] <i>So. that's how I came
to Chimney Rock.</i>

64
00:03:43.332 --> 00:03:45.164
<i>Daniel in the lion's den.</i>

65
00:03:45.165 --> 00:03:47.000
<i>David facing off Goliath.</i>

66
00:03:47.500 --> 00:03:49.914
<i>Young. dumb. and full of Christ.</i>

67
00:03:49.915 --> 00:03:51.748
<i>Ready for anything.</i>

68
00:03:51.750 --> 00:03:54.206
[door creaks. closes]

69
00:03:54.207 --> 00:03:56.290
[intriguing music continues]

70
00:03:59.250 --> 00:04:00.290
[bag thuds]

71
00:04:04.082 --> 00:04:05.082
[music fades]

72
00:04:09.875 --> 00:04:12.290
[door creaking]

73
00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:24.875
Father Jefferson?

74
00:04:25.790 --> 00:04:28.081
Hello. Jud Duplenticy from Albany?

75
00:04:28.082 --> 00:04:30.875
Lord be with you.
Jud Duplenticy from Albany.

76
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.125
You here to take my church away from me?

77
00:04:37.457 --> 00:04:39.250
[chuckling] Oh. No.

78
00:04:39.832 --> 00:04:40.707
Good.

79
00:04:41.582 --> 00:04:44.000
Okay. call me Monsignor Wicks.

80
00:04:44.915 --> 00:04:46.207
I see you've met Martha.

81
00:04:47.082 --> 00:04:48.331
Martha? No.

82
00:04:48.332 --> 00:04:49.915
- Monsignor Wicks.
- Jesus!

83
00:04:49.915 --> 00:04:52.499
- I woke up early to polish the silver.
- [sighs]

84
00:04:52.500 --> 00:04:53.874
It was a bit blotchy.

85
00:04:53.875 --> 00:04:55.499
That'll be fine. Martha.

86
00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:57.790
Father... Jud.

87
00:04:59.082 --> 00:05:00.375
You are welcome here.

88
00:05:00.875 --> 00:05:02.499
- Thank you. Martha.
- Mm.

89
00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:05.206
I was actually
just saying to Father Wicks...

90
00:05:05.208 --> 00:05:06.875
Monsignor Wicks.

91
00:05:07.708 --> 00:05:09.583
Monsignor. right. Sorry. [chuckles]

92
00:05:10.083 --> 00:05:11.708
And sorry for saying "Jesus".

93
00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:15.665
Hoo. [chuckles]
This is going great. I think.

94
00:05:15.665 --> 00:05:18.290
- Bishop Langstrom sent you. huh?
- Mm-hmm.

95
00:05:19.165 --> 00:05:20.250
Langstrom.

96
00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:22.415
- I know him well.
- [chuckles]

97
00:05:22.415 --> 00:05:24.707
He handpicked you. sent you here.

98
00:05:25.500 --> 00:05:27.000
It says something to me.

99
00:05:29.582 --> 00:05:30.790
Tells me a lot.

100
00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:34.707
Well. I... I know
you're used to flying solo. but. um...

101
00:05:35.290 --> 00:05:36.915
I'm... I'm here to serve.

102
00:05:38.415 --> 00:05:39.625
Take my confession.

103
00:05:41.290 --> 00:05:43.082
[Wicks groans] All right.

104
00:05:43.790 --> 00:05:45.082
- Mm.
- [chuckles]

105
00:05:47.165 --> 00:05:49.706
Bless me. Father. for I have sinned.

106
00:05:49.707 --> 00:05:51.000
It's been. uh.

107
00:05:51.875 --> 00:05:54.290
six weeks since my last confession.

108
00:05:55.040 --> 00:05:57.082
[inhales deeply. sighs]

109
00:05:58.707 --> 00:06:01.250
I've envied the material wealth of others.

110
00:06:02.125 --> 00:06:06.750
I saw this luxury car commercial.
Sam had it on his TV. Lexus.

111
00:06:07.415 --> 00:06:08.625
And I thought.

112
00:06:09.125 --> 00:06:11.874
- "Ah! That is a good-looking car."
- [both chuckle]

113
00:06:11.875 --> 00:06:13.458
The coupe.

114
00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:17.957
Uh... I've envied the power of great men.

115
00:06:19.375 --> 00:06:22.749
Envied my grandfather's power as a priest.
I wanted that.

116
00:06:22.750 --> 00:06:24.040
Always did.

117
00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:26.790
Uh...

118
00:06:27.540 --> 00:06:28.957
I've masturbated.

119
00:06:30.165 --> 00:06:33.706
um. four times this week.

120
00:06:33.707 --> 00:06:36.624
Four or five. generally. in...
What'd I say. six weeks?

121
00:06:36.625 --> 00:06:39.790
Well. let's say 30 times. masturbated.

122
00:06:40.832 --> 00:06:44.457
Uh. this week. in my bed.
in the morning once.

123
00:06:44.957 --> 00:06:49.040
Once in the shower. standing up.
which was convenient.

124
00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:51.249
Just use a bath gel.

125
00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:52.249
[inhales deeply]

126
00:06:52.250 --> 00:06:55.540
Oh. once in the middle of the night.
after a dream about--

127
00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:58.206
- That's all right.
- About one of those Japanese cat cafÃ©s.

128
00:06:58.207 --> 00:07:00.624
- Okay.
- You know. I read this article.

129
00:07:00.625 --> 00:07:05.915
but the cats were girls.
and. you know. so...

130
00:07:06.583 --> 00:07:07.999
And I hadn't prepared.

131
00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.125
so I had to finish into a copy
of <i>Catholic Chronicle</i> magazine.

132
00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:16.915
just what was on the end table.
which is probably its own kind of sin.

133
00:07:17.415 --> 00:07:20.415
I don't know. maybe not. but...
Not good. [chuckles]

134
00:07:21.540 --> 00:07:23.831
[Jud] <i>At the time.
I thought this was just weird.</i>

135
00:07:23.832 --> 00:07:24.749
[imperceptible]

136
00:07:24.750 --> 00:07:26.915
<i>But looking back now. I know.</i>

137
00:07:26.915 --> 00:07:29.331
<i>This was Wicks' first punch.</i>

138
00:07:29.332 --> 00:07:31.457
Five Hail Marys and one Glory Be.

139
00:07:33.165 --> 00:07:34.457
Thank you. Father.

140
00:07:40.040 --> 00:07:41.540
[Jud] <i>It wouldn't be his last.</i>

141
00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:42.875
[Wicks] Oh. and welcome

142
00:07:43.665 --> 00:07:45.082
to <i>my</i> church.

143
00:07:45.915 --> 00:07:48.665
- [door opens. closes]
- [sighs]

144
00:07:48.665 --> 00:07:51.206
<i>Over the next few weeks. I settled in</i>

145
00:07:51.207 --> 00:07:53.500
<i>at Our Lady of Perpetual Fortitude.</i>

146
00:07:54.332 --> 00:07:56.665
[intriguing music plays]

147
00:07:59.165 --> 00:08:03.790
<i>The only other full-time employee
was the groundskeeper. Samson.</i>

148
00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:05.583
<i>Sam.</i>

149
00:08:11.125 --> 00:08:12.831
[Sam] <i>It's Monsignor Wicks</i>

150
00:08:12.833 --> 00:08:17.000
who gives me the strength every day
to not go back to the bottle.

151
00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:19.040
He used to drink too.

152
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:20.040
[music fades]

153
00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:24.082
But he said to me once.
"If I can stave off that demon. you can."

154
00:08:25.375 --> 00:08:27.290
And every day. it is a struggle.

155
00:08:28.165 --> 00:08:29.250
But I have.

156
00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:34.039
I credit him and... my sweet Martha.

157
00:08:34.040 --> 00:08:36.624
Your... your sweet Martha?

158
00:08:36.625 --> 00:08:38.332
I'd do anything for her.

159
00:08:39.707 --> 00:08:42.081
- My angel on Earth.
- [organ music playing]

160
00:08:42.082 --> 00:08:45.456
[Jud] <i>As far as the church goes.
Martha does it all.</i>

161
00:08:45.457 --> 00:08:48.749
<i>She keeps the books.
manages donations. files everything.</i>

162
00:08:48.750 --> 00:08:49.957
File that.

163
00:08:50.540 --> 00:08:52.956
<i>She launders the vestments.
stocks the supplies.</i>

164
00:08:52.957 --> 00:08:55.165
<i>feeds Wicks. plays the organ.</i>

165
00:08:58.875 --> 00:09:00.791
<i>She knew where the bodies were buried.</i>

166
00:09:01.582 --> 00:09:03.664
- So this is the crypt?
- [Sam] Yep.

167
00:09:03.666 --> 00:09:06.707
It's a damn shame.
Gotta put up a security camera.

168
00:09:07.207 --> 00:09:09.332
- [Jud] Is there an entrance?
- There is.

169
00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:11.707
This right here.

170
00:09:12.207 --> 00:09:13.332
it's a Lazarus door.

171
00:09:14.041 --> 00:09:16.914
Takes construction equipment
to open from the outside.

172
00:09:16.916 --> 00:09:19.875
But cantilevered as such that one push

173
00:09:20.457 --> 00:09:22.875
will send it tumbling
to the ground from inside.

174
00:09:24.125 --> 00:09:25.456
Who's in there then?

175
00:09:25.457 --> 00:09:26.541
- Prentice.
- [gasps]

176
00:09:27.166 --> 00:09:30.625
Wicks' grandfather.
the founder of this church.

177
00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:33.000
Was like a father to me.

178
00:09:33.665 --> 00:09:35.664
Makes me sick.

179
00:09:35.665 --> 00:09:40.000
These kids painting rocket ships
all over his sacred resting place.

180
00:09:46.707 --> 00:09:49.415
- [Wicks] What are you doing?
- Oh. uh...

181
00:09:50.207 --> 00:09:52.124
Well. I do a little wood-working.

182
00:09:52.125 --> 00:09:55.706
so thought I could borrow
some of Sam's tools. make a proper--

183
00:09:55.707 --> 00:09:56.999
No. we leave that.

184
00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.957
A reminder of the shameful sin
of the harlot whore.

185
00:10:01.500 --> 00:10:02.916
Take my confession.

186
00:10:04.875 --> 00:10:06.625
[Martha] Yes. the harlot whore.

187
00:10:08.125 --> 00:10:09.624
That was Wicks' mother.

188
00:10:09.625 --> 00:10:12.331
Okay. so what's the deal with that?

189
00:10:12.332 --> 00:10:14.625
She was a harlot and a whore.

190
00:10:15.457 --> 00:10:16.289
Okay.

191
00:10:16.291 --> 00:10:19.581
When Prentice entered the priesthood
and founded this church.

192
00:10:19.582 --> 00:10:21.832
he was widowed with a daughter.

193
00:10:22.957 --> 00:10:24.541
Grace was her name.

194
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:26.749
Always a bad seed.

195
00:10:26.750 --> 00:10:32.164
She loved revealing clothes
and her fancy brands.

196
00:10:32.165 --> 00:10:33.874
Fancy brands... Oof.

197
00:10:33.875 --> 00:10:35.039
- Mm.
- Yeah.

198
00:10:35.040 --> 00:10:37.956
As a teenager. she slutted around bars.

199
00:10:37.957 --> 00:10:40.249
was soon pregnant by a drifter.

200
00:10:40.250 --> 00:10:41.164
[imperceptible]

201
00:10:41.165 --> 00:10:45.289
[Martha] <i>Prentice had
a vast family fortune in the bank.</i>

202
00:10:45.290 --> 00:10:48.414
- [intriguing music plays]
<i>- To protect his grandson. Wicks.</i>

203
00:10:48.415 --> 00:10:53.082
<i>he promised that
if Grace stayed under his roof.</i>

204
00:10:53.790 --> 00:10:56.915
the fortune would be willed to her.

205
00:10:57.915 --> 00:11:01.750
<i>And so the whore
waited for her father to die.</i>

206
00:11:02.666 --> 00:11:05.081
<i>Oh. it weighed on him heavily.</i>

207
00:11:05.082 --> 00:11:06.666
Martha. remember this.

208
00:11:07.832 --> 00:11:10.666
Wealth and the power that comes with it.

209
00:11:11.416 --> 00:11:12.666
is Eve's Apple.

210
00:11:13.916 --> 00:11:16.041
Temptation that leads to the fall.

211
00:11:17.291 --> 00:11:21.125
I must protect our loved ones
from its corrupting influence.

212
00:11:22.207 --> 00:11:23.625
at all costs.

213
00:11:24.375 --> 00:11:26.206
<i>His day came at last.</i>

214
00:11:26.207 --> 00:11:27.541
I was there.

215
00:11:28.625 --> 00:11:31.831
<i>I saw Prentice take his final communion</i>

216
00:11:31.832 --> 00:11:34.664
<i>and die on the holy altar.</i>

217
00:11:34.665 --> 00:11:36.165
<i>At peace.</i>

218
00:11:36.957 --> 00:11:40.457
The harlot whore
went straight to Prentice's attorney.

219
00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:44.125
"Give me my money." she said.

220
00:11:45.375 --> 00:11:46.832
And do you know what he said?

221
00:11:47.957 --> 00:11:52.457
"Yes. you are heir
to every single penny Prentice had."

222
00:11:53.250 --> 00:11:54.875
And in his accounts.

223
00:11:56.165 --> 00:11:59.165
not one hot dime.

224
00:11:59.875 --> 00:12:02.039
Mm. what did he do with the fortune?

225
00:12:02.041 --> 00:12:04.041
Gave it to the poor. say some.

226
00:12:04.666 --> 00:12:07.541
Threw it in the ocean. say others.
No one knows.

227
00:12:08.416 --> 00:12:09.416
It was gone.

228
00:12:10.375 --> 00:12:14.207
That holy man's final act of grace

229
00:12:15.332 --> 00:12:19.625
was to keep the corrupting evil
out of wicked hands.

230
00:12:20.666 --> 00:12:22.500
All that he left her...

231
00:12:25.541 --> 00:12:26.541
was this.

232
00:12:27.166 --> 00:12:29.207
"What is this?" she said.

233
00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:31.707
But I knew.

234
00:12:32.415 --> 00:12:34.250
Look not for Eve's Apple.

235
00:12:34.915 --> 00:12:38.331
Your inheritance is now Christ.

236
00:12:38.332 --> 00:12:40.582
[ominous music swells]

237
00:12:44.207 --> 00:12:46.832
[Martha] <i>That night. she had her revenge.</i>

238
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.999
<i>In a demonic rage.</i>

239
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:56.164
<i>- she defiled this holy place.</i>
- [grunts]

240
00:12:56.165 --> 00:12:58.624
[sinister music plays]

241
00:12:58.625 --> 00:13:00.081
[grunting]

242
00:13:00.082 --> 00:13:01.082
[screams]

243
00:13:01.916 --> 00:13:03.791
[grunts. yells]

244
00:13:07.041 --> 00:13:07.957
[grunts. yells]

245
00:13:11.416 --> 00:13:13.832
[Martha] <i>Blasphemy. desecration.</i>

246
00:13:15.416 --> 00:13:18.414
<i>- Evil incarnate.</i>
- [yells]

247
00:13:18.416 --> 00:13:19.707
[music fades]

248
00:13:21.250 --> 00:13:23.291
[Grace breathing heavily]

249
00:13:27.457 --> 00:13:28.416
[squeals]

250
00:13:29.166 --> 00:13:30.125
[grunts]

251
00:13:34.415 --> 00:13:35.457
[breath trembling]

252
00:13:37.207 --> 00:13:39.249
[low unsettling music plays]

253
00:13:39.250 --> 00:13:41.332
[breathing heavily]

254
00:13:43.290 --> 00:13:44.250
[sniffles]

255
00:13:47.250 --> 00:13:49.250
[thunder rumbling]

256
00:13:54.082 --> 00:13:56.456
[Martha] <i>I said. "Sister Grace.</i>

257
00:13:56.457 --> 00:14:01.457
<i>God. your Father.
will forgive you in His love."</i>

258
00:14:05.082 --> 00:14:06.082
[music fades]

259
00:14:07.541 --> 00:14:09.499
- [Martha screams]
- [yells]

260
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:11.331
- [grunting]
- [yelping]

261
00:14:11.332 --> 00:14:13.416
[menacing music plays]

262
00:14:16.541 --> 00:14:17.956
[yelling]

263
00:14:17.957 --> 00:14:19.541
- [music stops]
- She died.

264
00:14:20.082 --> 00:14:22.374
throwing herself against Prentice's tomb.

265
00:14:22.375 --> 00:14:24.125
[screams]

266
00:14:25.541 --> 00:14:27.541
[Martha] <i>Brain aneurysm. they said.</i>

267
00:14:28.750 --> 00:14:30.666
Struck down. I say.

268
00:14:31.541 --> 00:14:34.875
by God in His mercy.

269
00:14:35.957 --> 00:14:37.500
Holy shit.

270
00:14:39.665 --> 00:14:40.665
Sorry. sorry.

271
00:14:41.665 --> 00:14:42.914
[intriguing music plays]

272
00:14:42.915 --> 00:14:46.331
[Jud] <i>The darkness of that story
was the bedrock of this place.</i>

273
00:14:46.332 --> 00:14:48.664
- [Wicks speaks indistinctly]
- [Jud] <i>You could feel it.</i>

274
00:14:48.665 --> 00:14:50.081
And he asked. "Who told you..."

275
00:14:50.082 --> 00:14:54.500
[Jud] <i>So what would draw someone
to make this their spiritual home?</i>

276
00:14:55.082 --> 00:14:58.081
<i>The core group of regulars
all had their reasons.</i>

277
00:14:58.082 --> 00:15:00.124
<i>And these will be our suspects.</i>

278
00:15:00.125 --> 00:15:01.832
<i>So I should introduce them.</i>

279
00:15:02.500 --> 00:15:06.206
<i>Vera Draven. local attorney.
She was loyal and devoted.</i>

280
00:15:06.207 --> 00:15:07.666
- [lock chirps]
- [whistle blows]

281
00:15:08.625 --> 00:15:11.956
[Vera] My dad was
Wicks' attorney and drinking buddy.

282
00:15:11.957 --> 00:15:14.164
[chuckles] The boys.

283
00:15:14.166 --> 00:15:18.624
And so you became a lawyer so you could
take over his family practice?

284
00:15:18.625 --> 00:15:21.791
I became a lawyer because
I wanted to do great things in the world.

285
00:15:23.125 --> 00:15:25.957
- But this place is my dad's legacy.
- [spoon clatters]

286
00:15:26.707 --> 00:15:27.749
And he wanted me to...

287
00:15:27.750 --> 00:15:30.206
- Thank you.
- ...keep it going after he passed.

288
00:15:30.207 --> 00:15:32.706
So here I am.

289
00:15:32.707 --> 00:15:34.624
- Yo. yo. Hey. Vera.
- [door closes]

290
00:15:34.625 --> 00:15:37.039
- Hi. Oh. Thank you.
- Would you fill this up?

291
00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:39.624
[Jud] <i>Her adopted son. Cy.
just moved back home</i>

292
00:15:39.625 --> 00:15:42.414
<i>after trying and failing
to get a foothold in politics.</i>

293
00:15:42.415 --> 00:15:43.414
Hi.

294
00:15:43.415 --> 00:15:44.456
Hey.

295
00:15:44.457 --> 00:15:45.625
Okay.

296
00:15:46.665 --> 00:15:48.206
It's nice having him back?

297
00:15:48.207 --> 00:15:50.375
[intriguing music plays]

298
00:15:51.415 --> 00:15:54.414
[Jud] <i>When Vera was young.
just out of law school.</i>

299
00:15:54.415 --> 00:15:58.249
<i>her dad came home
with ten-year-old Cy. out of the blue.</i>

300
00:15:58.250 --> 00:16:00.664
<i>and told Vera she was gonna raise him.</i>

301
00:16:00.666 --> 00:16:02.166
<i>No questions asked.</i>

302
00:16:03.750 --> 00:16:07.416
<i>The whole town knew he was
obviously her illegitimate brother.</i>

303
00:16:08.082 --> 00:16:09.500
<i>But Vera accepted it.</i>

304
00:16:10.457 --> 00:16:11.749
<i>She did it.</i>

305
00:16:11.750 --> 00:16:14.414
I've given up a lot to... [inhales deeply]

306
00:16:14.416 --> 00:16:19.041
...be loyal to my dad
and to Cy and to Wicks.

307
00:16:20.375 --> 00:16:21.706
So I think that

308
00:16:21.707 --> 00:16:25.206
when my dad
is looking down on me from heaven.

309
00:16:25.207 --> 00:16:28.706
I think he is very... [inhales deeply]

310
00:16:28.707 --> 00:16:30.500
...pleased with me.

311
00:16:32.875 --> 00:16:34.290
So I guess that's nice.

312
00:16:34.957 --> 00:16:36.039
[Cy] <i>I came this close.</i>

313
00:16:36.040 --> 00:16:38.664
I was the GOP golden boy. the great hope.

314
00:16:38.665 --> 00:16:41.289
I've got connections and ins and outs.

315
00:16:41.290 --> 00:16:43.499
I was on the cusp.
but I just couldn't engage voters.

316
00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:47.499
I didn't... [inhales] have that
cult of personality thing. I guess.

317
00:16:47.500 --> 00:16:50.414
It's hard connecting with people
in a genuine way.

318
00:16:50.415 --> 00:16:52.206
- I know.
- [Jud] Mm-hmm.

319
00:16:52.207 --> 00:16:54.706
I tried everything. Believe me.
I hammered the race thing.

320
00:16:54.707 --> 00:16:56.999
I hammered the gender thing.
the trans thing.

321
00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.206
the border thing. the homeless thing.

322
00:16:59.207 --> 00:17:03.125
the war thing. the election thing.
the abortion thing. the climate thing.

323
00:17:03.916 --> 00:17:07.914
Thing about induction stoves.
Israel. library books. vaccines.

324
00:17:07.915 --> 00:17:11.082
pronouns. AK-47s. socialism. BLM.

325
00:17:11.083 --> 00:17:15.000
CRT. the CDC. DEI. 5G. everything.

326
00:17:15.708 --> 00:17:19.708
All of it I did.
Nobody. just nothing. [sighs]

327
00:17:20.458 --> 00:17:22.664
People are just numb these days.
I don't know why.

328
00:17:22.665 --> 00:17:25.624
[hesitates] Maybe we need to get back
to fundamentals. you know.

329
00:17:25.625 --> 00:17:29.164
basic building blocks
on how to genuinely inspire people.

330
00:17:29.165 --> 00:17:31.289
The basics.
like. show them something they hate

331
00:17:31.290 --> 00:17:34.039
and then make them afraid it's gonna
take away something they love?

332
00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:35.749
[soft intriguing music plays]

333
00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:37.124
[hesitates] Well. no.

334
00:17:37.125 --> 00:17:38.539
- [indistinct chatter]
- Vera.

335
00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:41.332
- [Jud] <i>Nat Sharp. the town's local doctor.</i>
- [imperceptible]

336
00:17:41.333 --> 00:17:43.625
<i>His life revolved around his wife. Darla.</i>

337
00:17:44.290 --> 00:17:45.957
<i>She was his everything.</i>

338
00:17:45.958 --> 00:17:47.874
- [music stops]
- Darla left me last week.

339
00:17:47.875 --> 00:17:49.625
[tuts] Oh. I'm sorry.

340
00:17:50.125 --> 00:17:53.000
Took the kids. moved to Tucson

341
00:17:54.165 --> 00:17:56.790
with some guy that she met
on a Phish message board.

342
00:17:58.790 --> 00:17:59.750
[smacks lips]

343
00:18:00.415 --> 00:18:01.624
Phish the band?

344
00:18:01.625 --> 00:18:03.125
I had no idea.

345
00:18:03.958 --> 00:18:06.874
- [somber music plays]
- [Jud] <i>Dr. Nat was spinning out.</i>

346
00:18:06.875 --> 00:18:10.789
<i>He wasn't successful enough.
rich enough. good enough for her.</i>

347
00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:13.000
<i>He would do anything to get her back.</i>

348
00:18:15.875 --> 00:18:17.124
[intriguing music plays]

349
00:18:17.125 --> 00:18:19.832
<i>The closest thing we have
to a local celebrity.</i>

350
00:18:19.833 --> 00:18:22.040
<i>the sci-fi writer Lee Ross.</i>

351
00:18:23.125 --> 00:18:25.040
<i>You probably know
at least some of his books.</i>

352
00:18:25.665 --> 00:18:28.082
The Crescent Limbo <i>series.</i>
Ice Pick of Time.

353
00:18:28.083 --> 00:18:29.500
The Crystaline Juncture.

354
00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:32.789
<i>Ten years ago.
Lee moved here from New York.</i>

355
00:18:32.790 --> 00:18:35.874
<i>connected with Wicks and the church.
and as he puts it...</i>

356
00:18:35.875 --> 00:18:37.457
Unplugged my brain. you know.

357
00:18:37.458 --> 00:18:41.958
from the... [inhales] liberal hive mind
and... [exhales] come here and...

358
00:18:42.875 --> 00:18:46.833
[Jud] <i>His book sales and popular standing
have been in slow decline ever since.</i>

359
00:18:47.958 --> 00:18:51.374
<i>But he'd spent the last year
writing a massive book about Wicks.</i>

360
00:18:51.375 --> 00:18:52.957
His teachings. my reflections.

361
00:18:52.958 --> 00:18:56.457
essays and recollections
of an acolyte at the feet of a prophet.

362
00:18:56.458 --> 00:18:58.707
[Jud] The Holy Man and the Troubadour.

363
00:18:58.708 --> 00:19:02.414
<i>I found it a tough read.
but he pinned all of his hopes on it.</i>

364
00:19:02.415 --> 00:19:05.874
This is my last chance ticket
out of Substack hell.

365
00:19:05.875 --> 00:19:08.625
I can't take it anymore.
My readers these days...

366
00:19:09.125 --> 00:19:11.539
I mean. they are survivalist freaks.

367
00:19:11.540 --> 00:19:14.249
They all look like John Goodman
in <i>The Big Lebowski.</i>

368
00:19:14.250 --> 00:19:15.583
[chuckles]

369
00:19:16.458 --> 00:19:18.124
[church bell tolling]

370
00:19:18.125 --> 00:19:21.290
This little shitwick. Cy.

371
00:19:22.040 --> 00:19:25.249
He's got his little influencer fangs
in the Monsignor lately.

372
00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:27.999
We don't like him. We're all like.
"Wicks. Be careful.

373
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:32.165
you gotta shake him off.
He's bad news. Opportunistic poetaster."

374
00:19:33.165 --> 00:19:36.789
We're gonna have to protect Wicks
from these leeching millennials.

375
00:19:36.790 --> 00:19:39.664
[Jud] <i>Simone was new to town.
and new to the church.</i>

376
00:19:39.665 --> 00:19:43.290
<i>- She'd been a world-class cellist.</i>
- [playing dramatic. somber tune]

377
00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.582
<i>Forced to retire five years ago
for health reasons.</i>

378
00:19:49.583 --> 00:19:52.499
<i>Chronic pain. Some mysterious nerve thing</i>

379
00:19:52.500 --> 00:19:54.832
<i>- that doctors cannot diagnose.</i>
- Sorry. [panting]

380
00:19:54.833 --> 00:19:57.082
I believed they could heal me.

381
00:19:57.083 --> 00:19:58.790
[clicks tongue] Suckered.

382
00:19:59.290 --> 00:20:00.707
Dipshit <i>moi.</i>

383
00:20:00.708 --> 00:20:02.164
[breathes deeply]

384
00:20:02.165 --> 00:20:04.499
I mean. to take someone's faith

385
00:20:04.500 --> 00:20:06.208
and exploit it for money

386
00:20:08.083 --> 00:20:09.500
is the ultimate evil.

387
00:20:11.750 --> 00:20:13.164
Don't you think it is?

388
00:20:13.165 --> 00:20:15.375
Yeah. Yeah. it's bad.

389
00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:18.915
But I understand wanting to believe.

390
00:20:20.958 --> 00:20:22.582
This feels different. though.

391
00:20:22.583 --> 00:20:24.332
[intriguing music plays]

392
00:20:24.333 --> 00:20:26.833
Faith in God to heal me.

393
00:20:29.040 --> 00:20:30.250
This is different.

394
00:20:33.625 --> 00:20:36.250
I feel hopeful now.

395
00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:40.415
Like a miracle could happen.

396
00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:45.915
That's how Monsignor Wicks makes me feel.

397
00:20:49.750 --> 00:20:52.125
- [intriguing music continues]
- [wind gusting]

398
00:20:55.040 --> 00:20:56.707
[indistinct chatter]

399
00:20:56.708 --> 00:20:59.708
- The Spirit really moved him today. huh?
- [gasps]

400
00:21:00.958 --> 00:21:02.165
Monsignor!

401
00:21:03.083 --> 00:21:04.333
Ah. my warrior.

402
00:21:04.915 --> 00:21:07.999
- [Jud] <i>Wicks kept his core group tight.</i>
- [laughs]

403
00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:11.583
[Jud] <i>And the seductive power
of his charisma was undeniable.</i>

404
00:21:13.665 --> 00:21:14.875
<i>But his method...</i>

405
00:21:15.875 --> 00:21:17.914
<i>Every week. he would pick someone out.</i>

406
00:21:17.915 --> 00:21:20.957
<i>a newcomer usually. and he would attack.</i>

407
00:21:20.958 --> 00:21:24.125
The world wants us all to be okay.

408
00:21:25.958 --> 00:21:29.790
Any of your choices.
Make your choices. They're your choices.

409
00:21:30.290 --> 00:21:31.500
Don't feel bad.

410
00:21:32.208 --> 00:21:33.500
Have that affair.

411
00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:35.207
Tell that lie.

412
00:21:35.208 --> 00:21:37.624
Have that child out of wedlock.

413
00:21:37.625 --> 00:21:40.500
Satisfy your selfish heart.

414
00:21:41.125 --> 00:21:42.539
Selfish.

415
00:21:42.540 --> 00:21:43.665
Yes.

416
00:21:44.208 --> 00:21:47.333
Depriving that child of a family.

417
00:21:48.250 --> 00:21:49.583
Of a father.

418
00:21:50.083 --> 00:21:52.289
An assault on our castle.

419
00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:54.374
The institution of manhood.

420
00:21:54.375 --> 00:21:56.914
My own mother made
that selfish choice with me.

421
00:21:56.915 --> 00:21:59.124
And I curse her selfish heart for it.

422
00:21:59.125 --> 00:22:01.624
Every day of my life.

423
00:22:01.625 --> 00:22:05.874
Putting her needs and wants
before the family God intended.

424
00:22:05.875 --> 00:22:07.165
I am enough!

425
00:22:07.750 --> 00:22:10.414
- Me!
- [tense music plays]

426
00:22:10.415 --> 00:22:14.415
Selfish. harlot heart. you are not.

427
00:22:15.208 --> 00:22:16.707
Might as well beat that child.

428
00:22:16.708 --> 00:22:19.457
Yes. might as well starve that child.

429
00:22:19.458 --> 00:22:22.374
Defy the family that the Lord intended.

430
00:22:22.375 --> 00:22:26.290
And watch your child
burn beneath that burden.

431
00:22:27.208 --> 00:22:29.124
- [music subsides]
- [imperceptible]

432
00:22:29.125 --> 00:22:31.333
[Jud] <i>This is not the true church.</i>

433
00:22:32.290 --> 00:22:35.374
<i>You ask even the most hardcore
of those in the pews.</i>

434
00:22:35.375 --> 00:22:38.124
<i>they'll say. no.
of course this is not what they believe.</i>

435
00:22:38.125 --> 00:22:40.957
<i>It's Wicks being Wicks.
pushing it too far.</i>

436
00:22:40.958 --> 00:22:44.957
<i>And what he's pushing for
every time is a walkout.</i>

437
00:22:44.958 --> 00:22:46.374
[intriguing music plays]

438
00:22:46.375 --> 00:22:47.875
<i>Why does he do this?</i>

439
00:22:48.458 --> 00:22:51.458
<i>Because when that person walks out.
everyone watches.</i>

440
00:22:52.040 --> 00:22:54.789
<i>And even if in the light of day
it's indefensible.</i>

441
00:22:54.790 --> 00:22:58.039
<i>deep down in the dark.
it scratches an itch.</i>

442
00:22:58.040 --> 00:22:59.915
[imperceptible]

443
00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:05.665
[Jud] <i>And by staying put in that pew.
a side is taken.</i>

444
00:23:06.915 --> 00:23:08.624
<i>Wicks' side.</i>

445
00:23:08.625 --> 00:23:11.707
<i>Testing tolerances.
tapping deep poisoned wells.</i>

446
00:23:11.708 --> 00:23:13.789
<i>hardening. binding with complicity.</i>

447
00:23:13.790 --> 00:23:17.332
[man over radio] <i>...for a two-run homer
and that brings the Cubs...</i>

448
00:23:17.333 --> 00:23:18.915
[grunts] Mm.

449
00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:22.582
- [Jud] <i>So I try to offer a counterbalance.</i>
- [music fades]

450
00:23:22.583 --> 00:23:26.039
Okay. welcome to our first
Father Jud prayer group.

451
00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:28.583
Um. thank you all for being here.

452
00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:32.039
And this is all about breaking down walls

453
00:23:32.040 --> 00:23:34.540
between us and Christ.

454
00:23:35.250 --> 00:23:38.083
us and each other. us and the world.

455
00:23:39.333 --> 00:23:40.958
When I was 17.

456
00:23:41.458 --> 00:23:42.999
I was a boxer

457
00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:45.583
and I... I... killed a man in the ring.

458
00:23:47.458 --> 00:23:49.375
I built up so many walls of...

459
00:23:50.040 --> 00:23:52.833
of anger. addiction. violence.

460
00:23:54.333 --> 00:23:56.540
It was only when I felt safe enough to...

461
00:23:57.125 --> 00:24:00.957
to put my dukes down. open my arms.

462
00:24:00.958 --> 00:24:03.125
um. confess my deepest sin.

463
00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:06.208
That was the day
that Christ saved my life.

464
00:24:06.958 --> 00:24:09.582
It... He didn't... He didn't transform me.

465
00:24:09.583 --> 00:24:12.374
He sustains me every day.

466
00:24:12.375 --> 00:24:13.874
[clock ticking]

467
00:24:13.875 --> 00:24:15.458
That's daily bread. right?

468
00:24:16.958 --> 00:24:19.083
I think that's what the church should be.

469
00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:22.415
That's what I want
this church to be. for me

470
00:24:23.083 --> 00:24:24.500
and for all of you.

471
00:24:29.165 --> 00:24:30.458
- [Vera chuckles softly]
- So...

472
00:24:33.625 --> 00:24:36.040
Monsignor Wicks isn't coming?

473
00:24:38.040 --> 00:24:39.665
[hesitates] No. but...

474
00:24:40.458 --> 00:24:41.457
No.

475
00:24:41.458 --> 00:24:44.624
So. I thought we could just talk
and start sharing and--

476
00:24:44.625 --> 00:24:46.332
But he knows that we're doing these?

477
00:24:46.333 --> 00:24:48.582
Sure. of course. Of course. I'll tell him.

478
00:24:48.583 --> 00:24:50.832
I just... I wanted us to connect and. uh...

479
00:24:50.833 --> 00:24:53.124
You'll tell him? You'll... You'll tell him?

480
00:24:53.125 --> 00:24:56.625
Contraction of the simple future tense
meaning you haven't yet

481
00:24:57.250 --> 00:24:58.458
told him?

482
00:24:59.415 --> 00:25:00.832
Why wouldn't you tell him?

483
00:25:00.833 --> 00:25:02.875
- This feels kind of weird.
- [Jud] Okay. guys.

484
00:25:03.458 --> 00:25:06.539
[chuckles] This is a prayer meeting.
It's... it's not a secret or anything.

485
00:25:06.540 --> 00:25:08.789
- Well. it's a secret prayer meeting.
- No.

486
00:25:08.790 --> 00:25:10.582
That's literally what it is.

487
00:25:10.583 --> 00:25:11.832
I just texted the Monsignor.

488
00:25:11.833 --> 00:25:14.332
Great. so... [chuckles]
it isn't a secret anymore.

489
00:25:14.333 --> 00:25:17.624
