1450
01:16:39.500 --> 01:16:41.750
- [door slams]
- Weak.

1451
01:16:42.582 --> 01:16:43.998
All of you.

1452
01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:46.289
You can't follow my path.

1453
01:16:46.291 --> 01:16:48.582
Yes. we are at war

1454
01:16:48.582 --> 01:16:51.125
and I cast you out of my fortress.

1455
01:16:51.707 --> 01:16:52.914
You son of a bitch.

1456
01:16:52.916 --> 01:16:55.873
On Easter Sunday.
when the pews fill with townspeople.

1457
01:16:55.875 --> 01:16:58.373
I will lay bare the sins of this flock.

1458
01:16:58.375 --> 01:17:02.875
Cut you loose and shake the dust
of this place off of my sandals.

1459
01:17:04.082 --> 01:17:05.291
And to hell

1460
01:17:06.625 --> 01:17:07.707
with you all.

1461
01:17:07.707 --> 01:17:09.791
[sinister music rises]

1462
01:17:16.957 --> 01:17:18.166
[music stops]

1463
01:17:21.416 --> 01:17:25.582
[inhales sharply] Well. glory be.
That cleared the room. [scoffs]

1464
01:17:25.582 --> 01:17:26.750
Cy.

1465
01:17:28.041 --> 01:17:30.123
- Why'd he do that?
- [sighs]

1466
01:17:30.125 --> 01:17:32.457
[Jud] Cy. Tell me. What was happening?

1467
01:17:32.457 --> 01:17:34.914
Why'd he torch them all?
Why would he do that?

1468
01:17:34.916 --> 01:17:36.332
Because I told him to.

1469
01:17:37.291 --> 01:17:39.916
When Vera told me the truth.
I went and found him.

1470
01:17:40.791 --> 01:17:44.000
<i>And he embraced me as a son
for the first time in my life.</i>

1471
01:17:44.750 --> 01:17:46.666
He unburdened himself.

1472
01:17:47.375 --> 01:17:49.375
[Wicks] I hate this place.

1473
01:17:50.541 --> 01:17:52.957
I hate this sad flock of losers.

1474
01:17:53.791 --> 01:17:55.416
I want to get out.

1475
01:17:56.207 --> 01:17:57.832
And now. finally...

1476
01:17:58.957 --> 01:18:00.166
I can.

1477
01:18:01.957 --> 01:18:03.166
He told me.

1478
01:18:03.957 --> 01:18:06.789
his grandfather's family fortune.
lost all these years.

1479
01:18:06.791 --> 01:18:09.082
he told me he found it. Just this week.

1480
01:18:09.082 --> 01:18:10.998
No. No. that money is gone.

1481
01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:14.789
Nobody knows where Prentice put it.
but it's gone without a trace.

1482
01:18:14.791 --> 01:18:17.498
- He told me he found it.
- [chuckles derisively]

1483
01:18:17.500 --> 01:18:20.625
[Cy] He was gonna shutter this dump
and retire in filthy wealth.

1484
01:18:21.291 --> 01:18:24.414
And I told him. "Are you nuts?"

1485
01:18:24.416 --> 01:18:27.289
Retire? Do you know the power
of what you do on that stage?

1486
01:18:27.291 --> 01:18:28.623
I've shrunk the flock.

1487
01:18:28.625 --> 01:18:30.375
[Cy] No. You've radicalized them.

1488
01:18:31.041 --> 01:18:32.082
That is power.

1489
01:18:32.875 --> 01:18:36.873
In a small town. there are only so many
witches to burn and zealots to activate.

1490
01:18:36.875 --> 01:18:39.373
Your flame lacks fuel.

1491
01:18:39.375 --> 01:18:40.875
But on the Internet.

1492
01:18:41.375 --> 01:18:42.582
wildfire.

1493
01:18:43.875 --> 01:18:45.082
This money.

1494
01:18:45.875 --> 01:18:48.707
Your cult of personality.
Are you kidding me?

1495
01:18:48.707 --> 01:18:50.332
Give me four years.

1496
01:18:50.332 --> 01:18:51.832
You could be president.

1497
01:18:52.916 --> 01:18:55.041
Together we can build a real empire.

1498
01:18:56.250 --> 01:18:59.250
As father and son.

1499
01:19:01.666 --> 01:19:03.082
Like in <i>Star Wars?</i>

1500
01:19:03.082 --> 01:19:05.957
- Yeah. Exactly. like the Rebels.
- Oh.

1501
01:19:05.957 --> 01:19:09.457
His ministry and my political instincts
fueled by enough money.

1502
01:19:09.457 --> 01:19:11.832
Can you imagine
what we could do in Christ's name?

1503
01:19:12.500 --> 01:19:14.123
Yeah. Yeah. I think I can.

1504
01:19:14.125 --> 01:19:17.539
First. I told him.
and I'll admit this is a little personal.

1505
01:19:17.541 --> 01:19:20.373
first I told him
we need to burn this flock.

1506
01:19:20.375 --> 01:19:21.832
They're a liability.

1507
01:19:21.832 --> 01:19:24.039
If they associate themselves with us.

1508
01:19:24.041 --> 01:19:26.998
show up on cable news.
even want a place in this thing...

1509
01:19:27.000 --> 01:19:29.332
We need to burn them off like leeches.

1510
01:19:30.250 --> 01:19:31.875
[Jud] <i>That's why he torched them all.</i>

1511
01:19:32.541 --> 01:19:34.375
'Cause of your petty vindictiveness.

1512
01:19:34.957 --> 01:19:37.500
One of them might have killed him for it.
You know that. right?

1513
01:19:38.082 --> 01:19:40.916
Getting back to this vast fortune.

1514
01:19:41.500 --> 01:19:42.789
So it's yours now?

1515
01:19:42.791 --> 01:19:44.625
- Technically. yes.
- Technically?

1516
01:19:45.207 --> 01:19:47.416
- He didn't tell you where it was.
- [Cy] No.

1517
01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:50.207
His accounts are empty. There's nothing.

1518
01:19:51.082 --> 01:19:51.957
So where is it?

1519
01:19:52.707 --> 01:19:55.289
And then. I realized. 50 years ago.

1520
01:19:55.291 --> 01:19:59.125
what was the safest way
for Prentice to hide $80 million?

1521
01:19:59.707 --> 01:20:02.500
- A Swiss bank account.
- [Benoit] Aha!

1522
01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:06.416
And so all you need to do
is find that account number.

1523
01:20:07.332 --> 01:20:08.748
No luck there?

1524
01:20:08.750 --> 01:20:11.582
[sighs in exasperation] It has to be
written down somewhere.

1525
01:20:11.582 --> 01:20:13.914
Martha files everything and it isn't here.

1526
01:20:13.916 --> 01:20:15.207
I don't know.

1527
01:20:15.791 --> 01:20:18.664
Here. I thought it might be a code
because he kept saying.

1528
01:20:18.666 --> 01:20:20.539
"Eve's Apple
would be restored to the tree."

1529
01:20:20.541 --> 01:20:24.207
That was a thing.
As if Eve's Apple is the fortune.

1530
01:20:24.207 --> 01:20:26.748
But a Swiss account.
we're looking for 19 numbers.

1531
01:20:26.750 --> 01:20:28.041
so it doesn't work.

1532
01:20:28.582 --> 01:20:30.707
Vera. did he ever tell you anything?

1533
01:20:31.582 --> 01:20:34.707
Even if he did. I would go to my grave
before giving it to you.

1534
01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:36.582
Yeah.

1535
01:20:37.666 --> 01:20:40.914
You'd have done anything to keep
the prodigal son from getting the fortune.

1536
01:20:40.916 --> 01:20:42.207
It burns you up.

1537
01:20:42.916 --> 01:20:44.332
You bitter hag.

1538
01:20:45.375 --> 01:20:46.791
That money

1539
01:20:47.375 --> 01:20:52.791
is one psalm in the Bible
of my bitterness. you fucking child.

1540
01:20:53.457 --> 01:20:57.541
You should come and get your shit.
it'll be out on the street. [scoffs]

1541
01:21:01.000 --> 01:21:03.123
[door opens. closes]

1542
01:21:03.125 --> 01:21:06.623
You. You're a detective. I'll pay you.
I don't care. this is very important.

1543
01:21:06.625 --> 01:21:09.539
my inheritance
and future political career depends on it.

1544
01:21:09.541 --> 01:21:11.748
Can you think of anything

1545
01:21:11.750 --> 01:21:15.250
related to Eve's Apple
that might contain that number?

1546
01:21:17.207 --> 01:21:20.291
Oh. um... Mm-mm. [sniffles]

1547
01:21:20.916 --> 01:21:22.748
But if you think of anything.
you'll call me?

1548
01:21:22.750 --> 01:21:24.832
- Oh. yeah. You bet.
- All right.

1549
01:21:25.625 --> 01:21:26.789
[engine starts]

1550
01:21:26.791 --> 01:21:28.916
[intriguing music plays]

1551
01:21:32.207 --> 01:21:33.541
We should look everywhere.

1552
01:21:38.457 --> 01:21:41.541
It might be. uh. sewn in the lining.

1553
01:21:42.166 --> 01:21:44.457
- Etched in the metal.
- [ripping]

1554
01:21:53.957 --> 01:21:55.082
[Benoit sighs]

1555
01:22:00.166 --> 01:22:01.125
[hollow thudding]

1556
01:22:04.875 --> 01:22:06.166
This is hollow.

1557
01:22:06.750 --> 01:22:08.166
Yeah. Do it.

1558
01:22:16.082 --> 01:22:17.291
[sighs]

1559
01:22:24.125 --> 01:22:25.125
[sighs]

1560
01:22:25.791 --> 01:22:26.750
[clatters]

1561
01:22:29.625 --> 01:22:31.248
Remind me to file this.

1562
01:22:31.250 --> 01:22:32.541
File that.

1563
01:22:33.791 --> 01:22:35.748
- It doesn't make sense.
- I know.

1564
01:22:35.750 --> 01:22:37.873
An 80-million-dollar fortune.

1565
01:22:37.875 --> 01:22:39.707
But if Eve's Apple is the fortune

1566
01:22:39.707 --> 01:22:42.875
and it's not a pile of cash
in a Swiss account somewhere. what is it?

1567
01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:47.832
What?

1568
01:22:47.832 --> 01:22:50.000
They must have
misprinted the date on this.

1569
01:22:51.082 --> 01:22:54.582
It says the crypt opening thing
was ordered last Wednesday.

1570
01:22:55.250 --> 01:22:56.666
That can't be right.

1571
01:22:58.541 --> 01:23:01.750
Who would preorder burial equipment
for a man who isn't dead?

1572
01:23:03.125 --> 01:23:06.248
Someone who knew with great certainty
when their day and hour would come.

1573
01:23:06.250 --> 01:23:07.541
Give me that.

1574
01:23:08.582 --> 01:23:11.373
Oh. that's computer printed.
That's not a misprint. That's it.

1575
01:23:11.375 --> 01:23:13.914
Whoever called in that order.
that's the key.

1576
01:23:13.916 --> 01:23:15.582
- Okay. Yeah. Yeah.
- [line ringing]

1577
01:23:15.582 --> 01:23:18.082
- [telephone ringing]
- [pop music playing faintly]

1578
01:23:19.332 --> 01:23:21.457
Steel Wheels Construction. This is Louise.

1579
01:23:21.457 --> 01:23:24.082
Hello. Louise. It's Father Jud
from Perpetual Fortitude.

1580
01:23:25.250 --> 01:23:27.414
- Oh. Hello.
<i>- Hi. Louise.</i>

1581
01:23:27.416 --> 01:23:29.914
We had a piece
of your construction equipment here today.

1582
01:23:29.916 --> 01:23:32.582
- Uh. a forklift to open a. um... a crypt.
<i>- Oh. yeah. I know.</i>

1583
01:23:32.582 --> 01:23:35.039
<i>It's not too often
we get a crypt opening order.</i>

1584
01:23:35.041 --> 01:23:36.457
Great. So I need to know--

1585
01:23:36.457 --> 01:23:38.873
<i>I actually processed that order.
I do all the processing.</i>

1586
01:23:38.875 --> 01:23:40.623
Yeah. What I need to know. Louise. is--

1587
01:23:40.625 --> 01:23:42.707
<i>- I run this place with my brother James.</i>
- Right.

1588
01:23:42.707 --> 01:23:44.914
<i>- He takes orders but I process them.</i>
- Yeah. Right.

1589
01:23:44.916 --> 01:23:46.998
So the reason I'm calling. Louise. is to--

1590
01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:49.832
<i>I've been to that church of yours.
but I don't think you were there.</i>

1591
01:23:49.832 --> 01:23:52.914
- No. I... I'm new. relatively new here.
<i>- Congratulations.</i>

1592
01:23:52.916 --> 01:23:55.748
- Louise. I... I have to ask...
<i>- No. it was an older guy.</i>

1593
01:23:55.750 --> 01:23:58.207
<i>- Father... Is he...</i>
- Monsignor. Monsignor.

1594
01:23:58.207 --> 01:24:00.039
<i>- Father Monsignor. okay. well...</i>
- Louise--

1595
01:24:00.041 --> 01:24:03.623
<i>He was preaching when I went and
I gotta tell you. that is not a nice man.</i>

1596
01:24:03.625 --> 01:24:06.498
<i>- But I am sorry that he...</i>
- Okay.

1597
01:24:06.500 --> 01:24:08.998
<i>...yikes. died and.
you know. for all y'all's loss...</i>

1598
01:24:09.000 --> 01:24:11.498
Yeah. it's a terrible tragedy
for everyone. Louise.

1599
01:24:11.500 --> 01:24:13.998
Can I... I have to. uh. interrupt.

1600
01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:16.082
- I have a question.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

1601
01:24:16.082 --> 01:24:19.539
Uh. the order for the forklift.
I need to know who placed the order.

1602
01:24:19.541 --> 01:24:22.039
<i>- James takes the orders and...</i>
- James takes the orders.

1603
01:24:22.041 --> 01:24:24.707
<i>- ...he's left for the day.</i>
- Can I have James' number?

1604
01:24:24.707 --> 01:24:27.414
This is very important. We need to
find out who placed that order.

1605
01:24:27.416 --> 01:24:30.873
<i>- No. no. I don't think I can do that...</i>
- No. it's very important.

1606
01:24:30.875 --> 01:24:33.082
<i>- Excuse me. Father.</i>
- It's very--

1607
01:24:33.082 --> 01:24:35.164
<i>What I can do. as I was saying.</i>

1608
01:24:35.166 --> 01:24:38.123
<i>is I can get that information for you
and then I will give you</i>

1609
01:24:38.125 --> 01:24:39.832
<i>- a buzz back.</i>
- That's it. That's great.

1610
01:24:39.832 --> 01:24:42.539
And if you could call James now.
I would appreciate it so much.

1611
01:24:42.541 --> 01:24:44.539
- Thank you. Louise.
- And she'll call you back.

1612
01:24:44.541 --> 01:24:46.707
<i>I will. Hey. Father.
could I ask you something?</i>

1613
01:24:46.707 --> 01:24:49.000
Yeah. it's... Though. I mean...

1614
01:24:49.582 --> 01:24:51.082
Well. if you can make it quick.

1615
01:24:51.082 --> 01:24:54.123
- This is a priority for us right now.
- Maybe she could call you back and--

1616
01:24:54.125 --> 01:24:56.207
<i>Father Jud would you... Could you...</i>

1617
01:24:57.707 --> 01:24:58.789
Louise?

1618
01:24:58.791 --> 01:25:00.582
- [scoffs]
- [Louise] <i>Oh. God.</i>

1619
01:25:02.250 --> 01:25:03.332
Louise?

1620
01:25:03.957 --> 01:25:05.957
[sighs] <i>Will you pray for me?</i>

1621
01:25:09.500 --> 01:25:10.416
Uh...

1622
01:25:11.375 --> 01:25:13.000
Yeah. of course.

1623
01:25:14.416 --> 01:25:17.250
- Can I ask what for?
- [Louise sniffles] <i>Uh...</i>

1624
01:25:18.707 --> 01:25:20.332
<i>It's. uh. my mother.</i>

1625
01:25:22.666 --> 01:25:23.875
She's sick?

1626
01:25:24.625 --> 01:25:25.707
<i>Yeah.</i>

1627
01:25:25.707 --> 01:25:28.332
<i>Um. she's in hospice.</i>

1628
01:25:29.707 --> 01:25:31.332
I'm so sorry. Louise.

1629
01:25:31.332 --> 01:25:33.414
<i>Uh. she won't talk to me.</i>

1630
01:25:33.416 --> 01:25:35.582
<i>We fought last time we talked.</i>

1631
01:25:35.582 --> 01:25:41.457
<i>Uh. she has a tumor in her brain
that's affecting her.</i>

1632
01:25:41.457 --> 01:25:45.082
<i>and it's making her say
really terrible things.</i>

1633
01:25:45.082 --> 01:25:47.289
<i>and so I said bad things back</i>

1634
01:25:47.291 --> 01:25:50.082
<i>and now I'm afraid that
that's gonna be the last thing</i>

1635
01:25:50.082 --> 01:25:52.166
<i>that we ever say to each other.</i>

1636
01:25:54.832 --> 01:25:56.916
[tearfully] Father. I. um...

1637
01:25:58.832 --> 01:26:02.250
I'm feeling pretty alone. um. right now.

1638
01:26:05.541 --> 01:26:08.750
- [crying softly]
- I'm so sorry. Louise.

1639
01:26:10.082 --> 01:26:11.291
You're not alone.

1640
01:26:12.750 --> 01:26:14.166
I'm right here.

1641
01:26:14.957 --> 01:26:16.166
I'm here.

1642
01:26:17.041 --> 01:26:18.541
Can you tell me your mother's name?

1643
01:26:23.625 --> 01:26:24.916
[clicks tongue softly]

1644
01:26:26.166 --> 01:26:27.332
[sighs softly]

1645
01:26:27.332 --> 01:26:30.416
- [thunder rumbling]
- [wind gusting]

1646
01:26:32.875 --> 01:26:33.832
[inhales]

1647
01:26:34.875 --> 01:26:36.207
[exhales sharply]

1648
01:26:47.457 --> 01:26:50.082
I pray that Barbara
may feel her daughter's love.

1649
01:26:51.166 --> 01:26:55.000
That it will comfort her in this time.
and. Lord. I pray for Louise.

1650
01:26:56.416 --> 01:26:58.623
Be with her
and give her wisdom and guidance.

1651
01:26:58.625 --> 01:27:02.125
Hold her in your healing arms
and let her know she is loved.

1652
01:27:02.666 --> 01:27:04.291
She is not alone.

1653
01:27:04.916 --> 01:27:08.332
This we pray
through Christ our Lord. Amen.

1654
01:27:09.166 --> 01:27:10.125
Okay. Louise.

1655
01:27:10.750 --> 01:27:13.414
You have my number.
Any time. day or night.

1656
01:27:13.416 --> 01:27:14.791
I'm here for you.

1657
01:27:15.291 --> 01:27:17.248
- This church is here for you.
- [door opens]

1658
01:27:17.250 --> 01:27:18.500
Bless you. Okay.

1659
01:27:19.041 --> 01:27:22.041
[panting] Storm. I came to close up.

1660
01:27:23.791 --> 01:27:26.416
[Jud] I'll get the church.
You take care of the rectory.

1661
01:27:30.375 --> 01:27:32.623
- [wind gusting]
- Don't follow me. Blanc. I'm done.

1662
01:27:32.625 --> 01:27:34.539
And. uh. why exactly?

1663
01:27:34.541 --> 01:27:37.082
I've had a "road to Damascus" thing.

1664
01:27:37.082 --> 01:27:39.748
Paul had a holy revelation
on the road to Damascus.

1665
01:27:39.750 --> 01:27:42.707
Yes. I know. He was struck blind
and all that hogwash.

1666
01:27:42.707 --> 01:27:44.789
Probably just a case of pink eye.

1667
01:27:44.791 --> 01:27:48.373
But he was not on the verge
of solving a murder when it happened.

1668
01:27:48.375 --> 01:27:50.875
I mean. what do you think
we're doing here?

1669
01:27:51.541 --> 01:27:54.957
Why do you think I became a priest?
No bullshit. Really. Why?

1670
01:27:54.957 --> 01:27:58.123
- [wind howling]
- [thunder rumbling]

1671
01:27:58.125 --> 01:27:59.416
You felt guilt.

1672
01:28:00.000 --> 01:28:01.998
For taking a life. And the church.

1673
01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:04.914
it offered you a place to hide
and a clear method

1674
01:28:04.916 --> 01:28:07.000
to give you a sense of absolution.

1675
01:28:07.625 --> 01:28:10.500
The guy I killed in the ring. I hated him.

1676
01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:12.832
I remember. I knew he was in trouble

1677
01:28:12.832 --> 01:28:15.123
and I kept going and going
until I felt him break.

1678
01:28:15.125 --> 01:28:17.832
It wasn't an accident.
I killed him with hate in my heart.

1679
01:28:17.832 --> 01:28:20.248
There's no hiding from that.
there's no solving it.

1680
01:28:20.250 --> 01:28:24.164
God didn't hide me or fix me.
He loves me when I'm guilty.

1681
01:28:24.166 --> 01:28:26.373
That's what I should be doing
for these people.

1682
01:28:26.375 --> 01:28:27.748
Not this whodunit game.

1683
01:28:27.750 --> 01:28:29.082
No. now wait a minute.

1684
01:28:29.082 --> 01:28:30.541
[wind gusting]

1685
01:28:35.375 --> 01:28:37.582
Excuse me. Excuse me. I--

1686
01:28:38.332 --> 01:28:40.164
Would you look at me
when I'm talking to you?

1687
01:28:40.166 --> 01:28:42.248
We're looking for a murderer.
This is not a game.

1688
01:28:42.250 --> 01:28:43.707
It is a game!

1689
01:28:43.707 --> 01:28:45.414
Solving it. winning it.

1690
01:28:45.416 --> 01:28:47.539
Getting your big checkmate moment.

1691
01:28:47.541 --> 01:28:51.457
And by using me in it. you're setting me
against my real and only purpose in life.

1692
01:28:51.457 --> 01:28:54.164
Which is not to fight the wicked
and bring them to justice.

1693
01:28:54.166 --> 01:28:57.457
but to serve them
and bring them to Christ.

1694
01:28:57.457 --> 01:28:59.373
Otherwise. I'm just as bad as Wicks.

1695
01:28:59.375 --> 01:29:01.457
Making it about me and not Jesus.

1696
01:29:02.500 --> 01:29:04.914
Listen. you don't
have to understand. Blanc.

1697
01:29:04.916 --> 01:29:06.539
But just please.

1698
01:29:06.541 --> 01:29:08.914
please. please. please let me be.

1699
01:29:08.916 --> 01:29:12.625
- [intriguing music plays]
- [thunder rumbling]

1700
01:29:15.625 --> 01:29:17.457
- Can you say that again?
- No.

1701
01:29:17.457 --> 01:29:20.414
About making it about you. not Jesus.
Like Wicks. you said.

1702
01:29:20.416 --> 01:29:22.707
Father. this is important.

1703
01:29:22.707 --> 01:29:24.289
Help me understand!

1704
01:29:24.291 --> 01:29:27.375
We are here to serve the world.
not beat it.

1705
01:29:28.125 --> 01:29:30.332
- That's what Christ did.
- So?

1706
01:29:30.332 --> 01:29:33.248
So when Wicks was talking about
fighting the world for Christ's sake.

1707
01:29:33.250 --> 01:29:36.789
he wasn't talking about Christ.
he was talking about his own ego.

1708
01:29:36.791 --> 01:29:39.707
And power.
He was never talking about Christ.

1709
01:29:41.832 --> 01:29:45.039
Yes. over and over
he talked about Christ rising in power.

1710
01:29:45.041 --> 01:29:47.039
Getting his revenge on the unfaithful.

1711
01:29:47.041 --> 01:29:48.957
Eve's Apple is the treasure.

1712
01:29:48.957 --> 01:29:51.457
"Eve's Apple restored to the tree."

1713
01:29:51.457 --> 01:29:52.873
Now. what does that mean?

1714
01:29:52.875 --> 01:29:55.375
Blanc. I don't know.

1715
01:29:56.291 --> 01:29:57.916
And I don't care.

1716
01:29:58.541 --> 01:30:01.289
[sirens approaching]

1717
01:30:01.291 --> 01:30:02.875
[thunder rumbling]

1718
01:30:03.875 --> 01:30:06.623
That'll be Geraldine
coming for her update on the case.

1719
01:30:06.625 --> 01:30:09.332
Now. Father. you're right.

1720
01:30:09.332 --> 01:30:11.414
This is my game. not yours.

1721
01:30:11.416 --> 01:30:14.707
Why don't you head back to the rectory?
I'll handle her.

1722
01:30:16.291 --> 01:30:17.500
Thank you.

1723
01:30:18.207 --> 01:30:20.332
Make sure the door's shut when you leave.

1724
01:30:23.750 --> 01:30:25.582
Hope you catch your killer. Blanc.

1725
01:30:26.457 --> 01:30:27.832
Thank you. I... I will.

1726
01:30:27.832 --> 01:30:29.332
[sirens wailing]

1727
01:30:35.957 --> 01:30:37.957
[indistinct police radio chatter]

1728
01:30:45.250 --> 01:30:46.666
Father Jud?

1729
01:30:47.332 --> 01:30:49.082
- Father Jud.
- He's not here.

1730
01:30:49.082 --> 01:30:50.166
Come.

1731
01:30:50.666 --> 01:30:53.873
I want you to search those back rooms
and that closet thing too.

1732
01:30:53.875 --> 01:30:55.832
[thunder rumbling distantly]

1733
01:30:57.250 --> 01:30:58.082
Oh.

1734
01:30:59.166 --> 01:31:00.582
It's good. right?

1735
01:31:00.582 --> 01:31:01.957
[Geraldine] Great. actually.

1736
01:31:01.957 --> 01:31:04.373
Especially the part where
Gideon Fell walks you through

1737
01:31:04.375 --> 01:31:06.373
the possible solutions
of a locked-door crime.

1738
01:31:06.375 --> 01:31:07.414
- Mm.
- Yeah.

1739
01:31:07.416 --> 01:31:09.666
You covered three of them.
then you stopped.

1740
01:31:10.291 --> 01:31:12.500
Now. having read the fourth. I know why.

1741
01:31:13.125 --> 01:31:15.207
See. I rewatched the video
and I realized something.

1742
01:31:15.207 --> 01:31:16.332
[suspenseful music plays]

1743
01:31:16.332 --> 01:31:18.625
<i>From the moment Jud enters the closet.</i>

1744
01:31:19.125 --> 01:31:23.291
<i>until the first of the flock
has a line of sight into that closet</i>

1745
01:31:24.000 --> 01:31:25.416
is nine seconds.

1746
01:31:25.916 --> 01:31:28.750
Nine seconds alone and unseen.

1747
01:31:29.666 --> 01:31:33.500
<i>Plenty of time to do the deed
with a concealed knife.</i>

1748
01:31:37.166 --> 01:31:38.998
That's how it was done. right?

1749
01:31:39.000 --> 01:31:40.291
No games.

1750
01:31:40.791 --> 01:31:43.414
No bullshit. That's how it was done.

1751
01:31:43.416 --> 01:31:45.289
[thunder rumbling distantly]

1752
01:31:45.291 --> 01:31:47.041
- Yes.
- [scoffs]

1753
01:31:48.250 --> 01:31:50.873
And you knew. You knew all along
and you toyed with that poor kid

1754
01:31:50.875 --> 01:31:52.582
- like a cat with a mouse.
- No.

1755
01:31:52.582 --> 01:31:55.164
I don't have the whole picture just yet.

1756
01:31:55.166 --> 01:31:57.498
- If you could give me a little more time...
- No.

1757
01:31:57.500 --> 01:31:59.873
- I'm gonna be able to get--
- No!

1758
01:31:59.875 --> 01:32:02.375
I found my killer and I'm bringing him in.

1759
01:32:03.207 --> 01:32:04.416
Where is he?

1760
01:32:04.957 --> 01:32:07.916
- [thunder crashing]
- [wind gusting]

1761
01:32:12.750 --> 01:32:14.957
[slow suspenseful music plays]

1762
01:32:24.416 --> 01:32:26.500
[breathing heavily]

1763
01:32:27.875 --> 01:32:29.666
[muffled thudding]

1764
01:32:38.166 --> 01:32:40.332
[thudding continues]

1765
01:32:52.625 --> 01:32:55.332
[muffled thudding]

1766
01:33:02.625 --> 01:33:03.957
[deep rumbling]

1767
01:33:15.332 --> 01:33:16.875
[breathing heavily]

1768
01:33:40.582 --> 01:33:41.500
[Jud] Sam!

1769
01:33:42.000 --> 01:33:43.957
[panting]

1770
01:33:48.291 --> 01:33:49.541
[yelps. groans]

1771
01:33:53.625 --> 01:33:56.332
[panting]

1772
01:34:00.041 --> 01:34:03.041
- [ominous music plays]
- [high-pitched distortion]

1773
01:34:08.582 --> 01:34:10.582
[panting echoing]

1774
01:34:20.666 --> 01:34:22.332
[breathing heavily]

1775
01:34:26.125 --> 01:34:28.166
[rhythmic thumping]

1776
01:34:31.250 --> 01:34:33.082
[thumping accelerates]

1777
01:34:36.625 --> 01:34:38.666
[distorted yelling]

1778
01:34:49.541 --> 01:34:51.957
- [suspenseful music plays]
- [gasps]

1779
01:34:53.541 --> 01:34:56.248
[gasps. groans]

1780
01:34:56.250 --> 01:34:58.207
[panting]

1781
01:34:58.207 --> 01:34:59.500
[Benoit] Who's there?

1782
01:35:02.707 --> 01:35:04.250
[gasps. grunts]

1783
01:35:04.832 --> 01:35:06.041
Wait!

1784
01:35:13.625 --> 01:35:14.707
[Geraldine] Blanc?

1785
01:35:14.707 --> 01:35:15.875
Here.

1786
01:35:16.541 --> 01:35:19.457
[gasps] Oh. shit. Who's that?

1787
01:35:19.457 --> 01:35:21.375
The groundskeeper. Samson.

1788
01:35:22.875 --> 01:35:24.707
What the hell happened?

1789
01:35:39.125 --> 01:35:40.250
Oh...

1790
01:35:41.207 --> 01:35:43.707
[Benoit] Mm. [mutters. clears throat]

1791
01:35:44.957 --> 01:35:45.791
[Geraldine] Uh...

1792
01:35:49.625 --> 01:35:51.582
Mm. [clicks tongue] Yeah.

1793
01:35:51.582 --> 01:35:52.666
Okay.

1794
01:35:53.207 --> 01:35:56.623
Okay. Wicks was 100% medically dead dead.

1795
01:35:56.625 --> 01:35:59.125
I mean. we know this. I'm just...

1796
01:35:59.625 --> 01:36:01.041
just saying. right?

1797
01:36:02.332 --> 01:36:03.416
Right.

1798
01:36:05.666 --> 01:36:08.875
[Geraldine] Okay.
then I can also say out loud.

1799
01:36:09.457 --> 01:36:11.873
a man can't just rise from the dead.

1800
01:36:11.875 --> 01:36:14.791
I mean. there's obviously some
<i>Scooby-Doo</i> shit going on here.

1801
01:36:15.291 --> 01:36:16.707
"Scooby-Dooby-Doo."

1802
01:36:16.707 --> 01:36:20.623
Praise to God!
Praise and glory to the Almighty!

1803
01:36:20.625 --> 01:36:22.123
- Praise Him!
- [siren wails]

1804
01:36:22.125 --> 01:36:26.123
Praise God!
Praise and glory to the Almighty.

1805
01:36:26.125 --> 01:36:28.998
- He hath raised His Son.
- Hey. Ritz.

1806
01:36:29.000 --> 01:36:30.498
Set a perimeter on the road.

1807
01:36:30.500 --> 01:36:32.998
News is gonna spread fast
and I don't want any lookie-loos.

1808
01:36:33.000 --> 01:36:34.498
- You got it.
- Chief!

1809
01:36:34.500 --> 01:36:35.414
What?

1810
01:36:35.416 --> 01:36:37.623
That motion-detector light there.
it's also a camera.

1811
01:36:37.625 --> 01:36:39.957
But it's not hooked up to anything.

1812
01:36:39.957 --> 01:36:41.164
[Geraldine] A camera. huh?

1813
01:36:41.166 --> 01:36:43.748
I don't know. Maybe it's recording
something on a chip inside.

1814
01:36:43.750 --> 01:36:45.957
Why don't you bring it into the media lab?

1815
01:36:46.625 --> 01:36:48.207
Hallelujah. praise God.

1816
01:36:48.207 --> 01:36:50.707
He has raised up
His servant from the dead.

1817
01:36:50.707 --> 01:36:53.414
Hey. do me a favor? Tape off
this entire area. down to the grove.

1818
01:36:53.416 --> 01:36:54.914
- Got it.
- It's a homicide scene.

1819
01:36:54.916 --> 01:36:56.789
The groundskeeper is dead.

1820
01:36:56.791 --> 01:36:58.875
[somber music plays]

1821
01:37:04.832 --> 01:37:07.791
[screams. cries]

1822
01:37:08.957 --> 01:37:10.750
[sobbing] No! Please!

1823
01:37:11.791 --> 01:37:14.207
- Oh. shit.
- [Martha] No! No. no. no!

1824
01:37:14.207 --> 01:37:15.707
[Geraldine] Can I get some help?

1825
01:37:15.707 --> 01:37:17.789
- Get help! Martha.
- No! Oh. no. no!

1826
01:37:17.791 --> 01:37:20.082
- Martha. you need to back up.
- Oh. no!

1827
01:37:20.082 --> 01:37:22.539
- Martha...
- [sobbing]

1828
01:37:22.541 --> 01:37:25.664
Flee into the dark. you murderer!

1829
01:37:25.666 --> 01:37:27.623
- [panting]
- [dramatic music plays]

1830
01:37:27.625 --> 01:37:29.332
But he has returned!

1831
01:37:29.832 --> 01:37:33.541
And he brings vengeance! He brings death!

1832
01:37:34.291 --> 01:37:35.332
[grunts]

1833
01:37:35.332 --> 01:37:36.248
[sniffles]

1834
01:37:36.250 --> 01:37:37.750
- [panting]
- [music fades]

1835
01:37:39.707 --> 01:37:41.373
- [cell phone buzzing]
- [gasps]

1836
01:37:41.375 --> 01:37:42.791
[wind howling]

1837
01:37:46.916 --> 01:37:47.875
[cell phone clacks]

1838
01:37:50.750 --> 01:37:52.164
This is Father Jud.

1839
01:37:52.166 --> 01:37:54.666
<i>Oh. Father Jud. it's Louise.
How you doing?</i>

1840
01:37:56.000 --> 01:37:57.291
Uh...

1841
01:37:58.666 --> 01:38:00.291
Yeah... [hesitates] Hi. Louise.

1842
01:38:00.791 --> 01:38:03.207
<i>I... I hope it's not too late.
but you said it was urgent.</i>

1843
01:38:03.207 --> 01:38:04.914
<i>so I just wanted to tell you...</i>

1844
01:38:04.916 --> 01:38:07.623
<i>I spoke to James
and the order for the forklift</i>

1845
01:38:07.625 --> 01:38:10.332
<i>was actually placed by Monsignor Wicks.</i>

1846
01:38:11.207 --> 01:38:15.291
<i>He spoke to James directly about it.
so I do hope that this clears things up.</i>

1847
01:38:15.916 --> 01:38:19.332
<i>Hey. God bless you. Father.
and you have yourself a good night. okay?</i>

1848
01:38:19.332 --> 01:38:22.000
Uh... Yeah.

1849
01:38:22.666 --> 01:38:25.416
Yeah. you too. Louise. [pants]

1850
01:38:26.916 --> 01:38:27.832
[cell phone beeps]

1851
01:38:33.500 --> 01:38:35.166
- [sinister music plays]
- [yells]

1852
01:38:37.707 --> 01:38:38.916
[thunderclap]

1853
01:38:40.875 --> 01:38:42.332
[pants]

1854
01:38:48.250 --> 01:38:50.832
- [grunts]
- [cell phone ringing]

1855
01:38:50.832 --> 01:38:52.125
Jeez.

1856
01:38:53.916 --> 01:38:55.000
Yes?

1857
01:38:56.125 --> 01:38:57.957
Slow down. Martha. What?

1858
01:39:00.750 --> 01:39:02.664
- What?
- [thuds]

1859
01:39:02.666 --> 01:39:04.582
- [Lee] <i>It's a miracle.</i>
- Bullshit.

1860
01:39:04.582 --> 01:39:07.082
<i>No. it happened.
Martha said the tomb is empty.</i>

1861
01:39:07.082 --> 01:39:09.375
<i>I'm calling everyone. I'm on my way now.</i>

1862
01:39:15.291 --> 01:39:16.500
Did you. uh...

1863
01:39:17.041 --> 01:39:19.039
What are you doing? You don't smoke.

1864
01:39:19.041 --> 01:39:20.332
I did.

1865
01:39:21.166 --> 01:39:22.998
I smoked for 15 years.

1866
01:39:23.000 --> 01:39:25.000
Did Lee call you? Did he tell you?

1867
01:39:25.500 --> 01:39:26.707
Yep.

1868
01:39:27.957 --> 01:39:30.248
Okay. Well. I'm gonna go
witness a miracle.

1869
01:39:30.250 --> 01:39:33.416
- You enjoy your cigarette indoors.
- [door opens]

1870
01:39:35.082 --> 01:39:36.207
[door closes]

1871
01:39:36.207 --> 01:39:38.332
[vibrates]

1872
01:39:40.875 --> 01:39:43.707
- [heavy knocking on door]
- [slow suspenseful music plays]

1873
01:39:43.707 --> 01:39:45.291
[footsteps approaching]

1874
01:39:55.082 --> 01:39:57.082
[heavy knocking on door]

1875
01:40:05.082 --> 01:40:06.291
Praise be.

1876
01:40:07.416 --> 01:40:08.832
It's accomplished.

1877
01:40:08.832 --> 01:40:10.748
[vibrates]

1878
01:40:10.750 --> 01:40:13.875
- [line ringing]
- Come on.

1879
01:40:15.791 --> 01:40:17.500
- Come on. it's...
- [cell phone beeps]

1880
01:40:18.332 --> 01:40:19.541
He's got it.

1881
01:40:23.041 --> 01:40:26.123
All right. so... it's not great quality...

1882
01:40:26.125 --> 01:40:27.625
- It's fine.
- ...but. uh...

1883
01:40:38.457 --> 01:40:39.875
What am I looking at here?

1884
01:40:46.832 --> 01:40:47.832
Okay.

1885
01:40:47.832 --> 01:40:51.373
Um. yeah. so. it records
anytime there's motion

1886
01:40:51.375 --> 01:40:54.875
- and this clip is four seconds later.
- [mouse and keyboard clacking]

1887
01:41:07.041 --> 01:41:08.998
- Okay?
- [knock on door]

1888
01:41:09.000 --> 01:41:11.000
Prints from the gardening tool.

1889
01:41:12.291 --> 01:41:15.957
We didn't run the full database check.
just the suspects you questioned.

1890
01:41:16.666 --> 01:41:17.875
It's Father Jud.

1891
01:41:22.750 --> 01:41:23.957
Where is he?

1892
01:41:24.582 --> 01:41:26.416
I sincerely wish I knew.

1893
01:41:31.207 --> 01:41:33.748
[music intensifies. fades]

1894
01:41:33.750 --> 01:41:35.416
[chiming]

1895
01:41:36.375 --> 01:41:38.082
[thunder rumbling]

1896
01:41:38.082 --> 01:41:39.916
[indistinct police radio chatter]

1897
01:41:46.041 --> 01:41:47.875
Blanc. Blanc!

1898
01:41:48.500 --> 01:41:51.123
- I'm gonna do it. I'm gonna... turn myself--
- [shushes]

1899
01:41:51.125 --> 01:41:53.207
- [officer 1] <i>...388.</i>
- [officer 2] 388. en route.

1900
01:41:53.791 --> 01:41:54.791
[officer 1] <i>433.</i>

1901
01:41:55.625 --> 01:41:57.623
- I'm turning myself in.
- No you are not.

1902
01:41:57.625 --> 01:42:01.998
[on radio. loudly]
<i>â™ª Skimbleshanks. the railway cat! â™ª</i>

1903
01:42:02.000 --> 01:42:03.082
[Benoit clears throat]

1904
01:42:03.082 --> 01:42:05.914
I did it. I killed Samson.
I'm guilty. I have to confess.

1905
01:42:05.916 --> 01:42:07.082
- Let me out.
- Listen.

1906
01:42:07.082 --> 01:42:09.582
You're gonna tell me
exactly what happened. but right now.

1907
01:42:09.582 --> 01:42:11.289
how do I get to Dr. Nat's house?

1908
01:42:11.291 --> 01:42:12.875
- Dr. Nat?
- Yes. quickly.

1909
01:42:13.375 --> 01:42:14.582
I regret my stalling.

1910
01:42:14.582 --> 01:42:16.998
I only hope we're not too late.
Now. just get down!

1911
01:42:17.000 --> 01:42:19.250
[tires screeching]

1912
01:42:20.000 --> 01:42:21.332
[thunder rumbling]

1913
01:42:21.332 --> 01:42:23.539
Hail Mary. full of grace
the Lord is with you.

1914
01:42:23.541 --> 01:42:25.039
Blessed art thou amongst women...

1915
01:42:25.041 --> 01:42:27.289
...sir. that I respect you.
I respect the badge.

1916
01:42:27.291 --> 01:42:30.582
But this is our church and I'm not telling
you that I'm gonna resort to violence.

1917
01:42:30.582 --> 01:42:34.414
but we're gonna stay here all night
if we have to. We are seeing that crypt!

1918
01:42:34.416 --> 01:42:36.498
- Is it real?
- [Lee] They won't let us in.

1919
01:42:36.500 --> 01:42:39.166
[breath trembling] I need to see.

1920
01:42:39.875 --> 01:42:41.789
Please. I need to see.

1921
01:42:41.791 --> 01:42:43.332
[brakes screech]

1922
01:42:44.457 --> 01:42:46.332
[wind chime tinkling softly]

1923
01:42:48.832 --> 01:42:51.832
[slow suspenseful music plays]

1924
01:42:53.332 --> 01:42:54.875
[door creaking]

1925
01:42:59.541 --> 01:43:00.750
Dr. Nat?

1926
01:43:12.500 --> 01:43:14.082
[glass crunching underfoot]

1927
01:43:30.000 --> 01:43:31.166
[sighs heavily]

1928
01:43:35.625 --> 01:43:37.832
[sniffs. gags] Oh. God.

1929
01:43:38.582 --> 01:43:39.998
What's that smell?

1930
01:43:40.000 --> 01:43:41.791
[Jud breathing heavily]

1931
01:43:45.375 --> 01:43:47.000
Just wait here.

1932
01:43:49.041 --> 01:43:50.125
Blanc.

1933
01:43:50.666 --> 01:43:51.750
[Benoit] Yep.

1934
01:43:53.582 --> 01:43:54.416
[switch clicks]

1935
01:43:55.166 --> 01:43:56.623
[grim music plays]

1936
01:43:56.625 --> 01:43:58.125
Oh. God.

1937
01:44:11.332 --> 01:44:12.416
Right.

1938
01:44:14.082 --> 01:44:18.750
[inhales sharply]
Oh. Lord. that is... [coughs]

1939
01:44:20.957 --> 01:44:23.291
[groaning]

1940
01:44:30.166 --> 01:44:31.248
[Jud] Wicks.

1941
01:44:31.250 --> 01:44:33.500
[Benoit] Yeah. that's... It's him.

1942
01:44:34.375 --> 01:44:35.791
- [Jud] Is he...
- Yeah.

1943
01:44:36.500 --> 01:44:39.957
I mean. for what it's worth
these days. [clears throat]

1944
01:44:42.582 --> 01:44:44.707
Let's see now. Let's...

1945
01:44:45.875 --> 01:44:46.707
[groans]

1946
01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:49.250
Okay.

1947
01:44:50.750 --> 01:44:53.082
This might get unpleasant.

1948
01:44:53.082 --> 01:44:54.791
I mean. more unpleasant.

1949
01:44:55.332 --> 01:44:57.291
- [squeaks]
- [liquid draining]

1950
01:45:04.207 --> 01:45:06.207
[dramatic sinister music plays]

1951
01:45:30.332 --> 01:45:31.416
Dr. Nat.

1952
01:45:32.666 --> 01:45:35.500
In the flesh. Yeah... Or. what's left of it.

1953
01:45:38.291 --> 01:45:39.291
[clears throat]

1954
01:45:40.250 --> 01:45:41.375
[Benoit exhales]

1955
01:46:06.457 --> 01:46:08.414
[line ringing]

1956
01:46:08.416 --> 01:46:10.500
Geraldine. it's... it's Blanc. Um...

1957
01:46:11.625 --> 01:46:13.789
Yeah. he's standing right here.

1958
01:46:13.791 --> 01:46:15.373
[hesitates] Listen to me.

1959
01:46:15.375 --> 01:46:17.623
You're gonna wanna come
to Dr. Nat's house.

1960
01:46:17.625 --> 01:46:21.125
[breathing heavily]
There's a body. Or two.

1961
01:46:22.250 --> 01:46:23.666
It's all here.

1962
01:46:24.166 --> 01:46:27.041
- Yes. yeah. It's... it's finished. yeah.
- [stair creaks]

1963
01:46:28.166 --> 01:46:29.666
[sighs] I'll call you back.

1964
01:46:30.957 --> 01:46:32.789
Father Jud. Wait. wait.

1965
01:46:32.791 --> 01:46:35.000
I killed Samson. I have to do this.

1966
01:46:35.625 --> 01:46:38.250
I have to do it of my own free will
or it won't mean anything.

1967
01:46:53.791 --> 01:46:57.914
[female officer over radio] <i>Plate check.
Copy that. Any available units to respond...</i>

1968
01:46:57.916 --> 01:47:00.125
Would you call Geraldine for me. please?

1969
01:47:00.625 --> 01:47:03.457
Say Father Jud's returned to his church
and he's ready to confess.

1970
01:47:04.750 --> 01:47:06.248
[door creaking]

1971
01:47:06.250 --> 01:47:07.457
[door thuds]

1972
01:47:20.041 --> 01:47:22.748
Father Jud.
I'm here to arrest you for the murder

1973
01:47:22.750 --> 01:47:25.082
of Monsignor Jefferson Wicks
and Samson Holt.

1974
01:47:25.082 --> 01:47:29.332
And you're a person of interest
in the death of Dr. Nathaniel Sharp.

1975
01:47:29.332 --> 01:47:30.832
[splutters] Nat is dead?

1976
01:47:32.041 --> 01:47:33.332
Murdered in his home.

1977
01:47:34.332 --> 01:47:36.832
We also recovered Wicks' body. It's over.

1978
01:47:37.332 --> 01:47:40.457
Anything you say
can be used against you in a court of law.

1979
01:47:40.457 --> 01:47:43.164
But if you'd like to confess to anything.

1980
01:47:43.166 --> 01:47:46.082
this seems like
a pretty great place to do it.

1981
01:47:48.250 --> 01:47:49.332
Yeah.

1982
01:47:52.375 --> 01:47:54.123
Years ago.

1983
01:47:54.125 --> 01:47:56.625
I murdered a man in a boxing ring.

1984
01:47:58.332 --> 01:48:00.375
I killed him with hate in my heart.

1985
01:48:02.500 --> 01:48:05.916
Last night. that same sin rose in me
and in a moment of

1986
01:48:06.875 --> 01:48:09.039
fear and rage. I--

1987
01:48:09.041 --> 01:48:11.416
["Overture" from
The Phantom Of The Opera playing]

1988
01:48:13.500 --> 01:48:17.539
I'm sorry. that was dramatic.
but I needed you to stop talking.

1989
01:48:17.541 --> 01:48:19.873
- No. Father Jud--
- I was about to explain to everyone...

1990
01:48:19.875 --> 01:48:21.707
- Sit down and listen.
- Stop talking.

1991
01:48:21.707 --> 01:48:24.748
Please. let him. You were continuing...
Continue. you said last night...

1992
01:48:24.750 --> 01:48:27.164
- In a moment of fear and rage...
- I was about to do it...

1993
01:48:27.166 --> 01:48:30.332
[dramatically] You shall not silence
the voice of the Lord!

1994
01:48:30.332 --> 01:48:35.332
But sit now and behold the wickedness
and shame of the guilty

1995
01:48:35.332 --> 01:48:38.250
laid bare before you all!

1996
01:48:51.000 --> 01:48:54.125
- [whispering] What are you doing?
- [clears throat]

1997
01:48:55.832 --> 01:48:57.123
[smacks lips]

1998
01:48:57.125 --> 01:49:00.414
Let us begin with Wicks' murder.

1999
01:49:00.416 --> 01:49:03.332
Right here on Good Friday.

2000
01:49:04.041 --> 01:49:05.875
The impossible crime.

2001
01:49:07.250 --> 01:49:09.873
And. Geraldine.
you were correct in your deduction.

2002
01:49:09.875 --> 01:49:14.123
When Monsignor Wicks collapsed
in that closet space. he wasn't dead.

2003
01:49:14.125 --> 01:49:16.332
He wasn't even stabbed. not yet.

2004
01:49:17.332 --> 01:49:20.748
The flask he kept stashed
in the breaker box

2005
01:49:20.750 --> 01:49:24.539
<i>was spiked
with a very powerful tranquilizer.</i>

2006
01:49:24.541 --> 01:49:26.414
- [suspenseful music plays]
<i>- He drank from it.</i>

2007
01:49:26.416 --> 01:49:28.373
Fortified himself.

2008
01:49:28.375 --> 01:49:31.664
<i>And within minutes.
fell to the floor. unconscious.</i>

2009
01:49:31.666 --> 01:49:34.707
- [flask clangs]
- [Benoit] <i>The clanky clunk.</i>

2010
01:49:34.707 --> 01:49:36.623
Leaving him defenseless

2011
01:49:36.625 --> 01:49:40.125
and giving the killer
their chance to enter the closet

2012
01:49:40.707 --> 01:49:42.375
and deliver the deadly blow.

2013
01:49:43.000 --> 01:49:44.207
I... I said that already.

2014
01:49:44.791 --> 01:49:45.623
Father Jud.

2015
01:49:45.625 --> 01:49:48.539
No. The knife was in his back
when I found him.

2016
01:49:48.541 --> 01:49:50.207
There's something in his back.

2017
01:49:50.207 --> 01:49:53.332
So how? When? It's impossible. I saw.

2018
01:49:53.332 --> 01:49:54.875
What did you see?

2019
01:49:56.082 --> 01:49:57.498
The red devil head.

2020
01:49:57.500 --> 01:50:00.789
<i>Blood you assumed was Wicks'.</i>

2021
01:50:00.791 --> 01:50:03.125
Now. I showed you
the answer to this. did you see?

2022
01:50:04.375 --> 01:50:05.664
Il Diavolo.

2023
01:50:05.666 --> 01:50:07.332
The pizza bar. The photograph.

2024
01:50:08.666 --> 01:50:10.666
<i>You thought you saw.</i>

2025
01:50:11.207 --> 01:50:13.123
<i>but that wasn't it. no.</i>

2026
01:50:13.125 --> 01:50:15.414
<i>It was a second identical lamp.</i>

2027
01:50:15.416 --> 01:50:18.375
<i>A second identical devil head.</i>

2028
01:50:19.707 --> 01:50:20.791
Yeah.

2029
01:50:23.791 --> 01:50:25.416
<i>And it was also missing.</i>

2030
01:50:26.041 --> 01:50:27.457
Two devils.

2031
01:50:27.457 --> 01:50:28.873
[Benoit] Yes.

2032
01:50:28.875 --> 01:50:30.166
Why two?

2033
01:50:31.041 --> 01:50:32.664
And why painted red?

2034
01:50:32.666 --> 01:50:34.164
It wasn't red though. It's red now.

2035
01:50:34.166 --> 01:50:36.998
[Benoit] The same red
as the Good Friday vestments.

2036
01:50:37.000 --> 01:50:38.914
The same exact red

2037
01:50:38.916 --> 01:50:42.082
as the mysterious thread
found in the closet.

2038
01:50:42.791 --> 01:50:46.582
<i>Because the second devil head
was there all the time.</i>

2039
01:50:46.582 --> 01:50:48.998
<i>Sewn to the back of his vestments.</i>

2040
01:50:49.000 --> 01:50:50.373
Hollow. light.

2041
01:50:50.375 --> 01:50:52.541
and filled with a small squib of blood

2042
01:50:53.125 --> 01:50:56.041
<i>- triggered by an RF remote.</i>
- [static crackles]

2043
01:50:57.000 --> 01:51:00.207
[Benoit] <i>Set off
at the exact right moment.</i>

2044
01:51:00.207 --> 01:51:01.125
[Jud] Monsignor?

2045
01:51:02.500 --> 01:51:03.375
The doctor.

2046
01:51:05.125 --> 01:51:06.414
<i>A voice of authority</i>

2047
01:51:06.416 --> 01:51:10.039
<i>who can wait for the discovery he needs
before taking charge.</i>

2048
01:51:10.041 --> 01:51:11.332
There's something in his back.

2049
01:51:11.332 --> 01:51:13.041
Wait. Don't touch it.

2050
01:51:15.332 --> 01:51:17.748
A moment of distraction presents itself.

2051
01:51:17.750 --> 01:51:19.166
[imperceptible]

2052
01:51:20.332 --> 01:51:22.332
<i>And the deed is quickly done.</i>

2053
01:51:23.832 --> 01:51:25.082
<i>His final task.</i>

2054
01:51:25.082 --> 01:51:29.498
<i>to remove the incriminating
drug-laced flask.</i>

2055
01:51:29.500 --> 01:51:32.416
<i>But where was it? It was gone.</i>

2056
01:51:33.541 --> 01:51:35.748
The one hiccup in his plan.

2057
01:51:35.750 --> 01:51:39.707
The result of a moment
of foolish grace by Father Jud

2058
01:51:40.291 --> 01:51:44.832
<i>who concealed the flask
to hide Wicks' drinking</i>

2059
01:51:44.832 --> 01:51:47.750
<i>and returned later to retrieve it.</i>

2060
01:51:50.082 --> 01:51:51.291
My God.

2061
01:51:51.791 --> 01:51:52.957
Nat.

2062
01:51:52.957 --> 01:51:54.250
Why?

2063
01:51:54.750 --> 01:51:56.998
[Vera] Wicks was going to scorch
the earth.

2064
01:51:57.000 --> 01:51:58.707
He was going to ruin him.

2065
01:51:58.707 --> 01:52:01.623
No. The bigger why.
The why that brought you here.

2066
01:52:01.625 --> 01:52:04.123
Why do all this insane. elaborate stuff?

2067
01:52:04.125 --> 01:52:07.082
The theatricality? The impossible crime.

2068
01:52:07.082 --> 01:52:08.375
Why?

2069
01:52:09.041 --> 01:52:10.248
Indeed.

2070
01:52:10.250 --> 01:52:12.832
Okay. so... if Dr. Nat killed Wicks.

2071
01:52:13.375 --> 01:52:14.373
who killed Nat?

2072
01:52:14.375 --> 01:52:16.291
Well. now we get to it.

2073
01:52:17.000 --> 01:52:19.748
Not some fiddly locked-door mystery

2074
01:52:19.750 --> 01:52:23.207
with devices and clues.

2075
01:52:23.207 --> 01:52:26.707
but a much. much larger scheme.

2076
01:52:26.707 --> 01:52:31.873
One whose roots
run to the bedrock of this church.

2077
01:52:31.875 --> 01:52:33.707
And one which draws me.

2078
01:52:33.707 --> 01:52:37.039
an unbeliever in every sense of the word.

2079
01:52:37.041 --> 01:52:40.041
into the realm of belief.

2080
01:52:41.666 --> 01:52:43.500
To understand this case.

2081
01:52:44.541 --> 01:52:48.623
I had to look at the myth
that was being constructed.

2082
01:52:48.625 --> 01:52:51.539
Not to solve whether it was real or not.

2083
01:52:51.541 --> 01:52:54.039
but to feel in my soul

2084
01:52:54.041 --> 01:52:57.250
the essence of that
which it strove to convey.

2085
01:53:00.541 --> 01:53:01.957
A holy priest.

2086
01:53:02.707 --> 01:53:08.123
Struck down by no man.
but by the hand of Satan himself.

2087
01:53:08.125 --> 01:53:11.625
Laid to rest
in the sealed tomb of his father.

2088
01:53:12.207 --> 01:53:13.625
but then risen

2089
01:53:14.332 --> 01:53:15.957
by the will of God.

2090
01:53:15.957 --> 01:53:18.039
Risen as something new.

2091
01:53:18.041 --> 01:53:20.123
No longer a fallible man.

2092
01:53:20.125 --> 01:53:24.041
but now a symbol
of the Lord's power over death.

2093
01:53:26.000 --> 01:53:27.625
His justice for the holy.

2094
01:53:28.125 --> 01:53:30.375
His vengeance for the wicked.

2095
01:53:33.166 --> 01:53:36.998
Okay. And now. what really happened?

2096
01:53:37.000 --> 01:53:39.082
- Yes. Yes.
- [intriguing music plays]

2097
01:53:39.082 --> 01:53:42.998
It is time to break this tawdry facade

2098
01:53:43.000 --> 01:53:47.082
of miracles and resurrections
and reveal what really happened.

2099
01:53:47.082 --> 01:53:49.582
It is time for Benoit Blanc's

2100
01:53:49.582 --> 01:53:52.750
final checkmate
over the mysteries of faith!

2101
01:54:06.207 --> 01:54:07.332
[exhales heavily]

2102
01:54:07.332 --> 01:54:09.582
[solemn string music plays]

2103
01:54:18.750 --> 01:54:19.582
[sighs softly]

2104
01:54:21.291 --> 01:54:23.291
Blanc. are you... Are you okay?

2105
01:54:25.416 --> 01:54:26.625
Damascus.

2106
01:54:27.666 --> 01:54:28.875
Damascus?

2107
01:54:30.250 --> 01:54:33.289
Like... a road to Damascus thing?

2108
01:54:33.291 --> 01:54:35.250
Yes. yes. Damascus.

2109
01:54:38.791 --> 01:54:40.416
Shit. [sighs]

2110
01:54:41.291 --> 01:54:42.375
Blanc?

2111
01:54:43.000 --> 01:54:44.082
[inhales. clicks tongue]

2112
01:54:44.082 --> 01:54:45.082
[exhales]

2113
01:54:58.916 --> 01:55:00.541
I cannot solve this case.

2114
01:55:04.500 --> 01:55:05.500
What?

2115
01:55:06.582 --> 01:55:09.373
Are you saying that
your conclusion. Benoit Blanc.

2116
01:55:09.375 --> 01:55:12.414
is that Monsignor Wicks
rose from the dead?

2117
01:55:12.416 --> 01:55:13.914
That it was a miracle?

2118
01:55:13.916 --> 01:55:18.123
I'm saying I cannot solve this case.

2119
01:55:18.125 --> 01:55:19.582
[cell phone clicks]

2120
01:55:19.582 --> 01:55:20.750
That works.

2121
01:55:21.250 --> 01:55:22.082
Thank you.

2122
01:55:24.457 --> 01:55:25.541
[Jud] Blanc?

2123
01:55:26.250 --> 01:55:28.664
If you know what really happened.
you should tell everyone.

2124
01:55:28.666 --> 01:55:32.457
Is this you sparing our faith
or being respectful or something?

2125
01:55:32.457 --> 01:55:34.748
Because we deserve the truth.

2126
01:55:34.750 --> 01:55:36.248
It is not.

2127
01:55:36.250 --> 01:55:37.539
[breath shaking]

2128
01:55:37.541 --> 01:55:39.250
I need the truth.

2129
01:55:40.541 --> 01:55:42.832
[scoffs] Can't you just

2130
01:55:42.832 --> 01:55:45.791
give us the answer?
Isn't that what all this is for?

2131
01:55:48.582 --> 01:55:51.539
And would you consider blurbing my book?

2132
01:55:51.541 --> 01:55:53.332
[hesitates] No.

2133
01:55:53.957 --> 01:55:56.500
[Geraldine] Okay. All right.
Show's over. Everyone out.

2134
01:55:57.332 --> 01:55:59.750
Out. Out.

2135
01:56:00.457 --> 01:56:02.164
[officer 1] Yeah. can you stand back. sir?

2136
01:56:02.166 --> 01:56:03.373
[indistinct chatter]

2137
01:56:03.375 --> 01:56:05.082
[officer 2] Okay. can we keep them back...

2138
01:56:05.082 --> 01:56:06.664
[mellow intriguing music plays]

2139
01:56:06.666 --> 01:56:09.582
I add another chapter
and then we're... we're ready.

2140
01:56:09.582 --> 01:56:11.998
We're ready to publish. Trust me. Alan.

2141
01:56:12.000 --> 01:56:14.707
Call Random House. everybody.
It's gonna be huge!

2142
01:56:17.832 --> 01:56:21.707
What we've witnessed is a miracle
confirmed by Benoit Blanc himself.

2143
01:56:21.707 --> 01:56:25.123
The world will know
what happened today here at Chimney Rock.

2144
01:56:25.125 --> 01:56:29.207
You can find out yourself.
Follow my YouTube channel @CyDraven...

2145
01:56:29.207 --> 01:56:30.500
What a mess.

2146
01:56:32.000 --> 01:56:34.416
I assume they'll arrest Father Jud now.

2147
01:56:35.000 --> 01:56:36.082
Yes.

2148
01:56:37.041 --> 01:56:38.666
I suppose they will.

2149
01:56:44.832 --> 01:56:46.332
What the hell was that?

2150
01:56:46.875 --> 01:56:48.875
Road to Damascus.

2151
01:56:49.582 --> 01:56:51.998
Scales fell from my eyes.

2152
01:56:52.000 --> 01:56:53.914
So what? Facts. schmacks?

2153
01:56:53.916 --> 01:56:56.539
You believe in God
and all this <i>mishegoss</i> is real?

2154
01:56:56.541 --> 01:56:58.457
No. no. God is a fiction.

2155
01:56:58.457 --> 01:57:00.541
My revelation came from...

2156
01:57:01.625 --> 01:57:03.041
from Father Jud.

2157
01:57:04.500 --> 01:57:06.916
- His example to have grace.
- [door opens]

2158
01:57:09.582 --> 01:57:11.416
Grace for my enemy.

2159
01:57:15.166 --> 01:57:16.541
Grace for the broken.

2160
01:57:19.000 --> 01:57:20.625
Grace for those who

2161
01:57:21.416 --> 01:57:22.541
deserve it the least.

2162
01:57:24.625 --> 01:57:26.041
But who need it the most.

2163
01:57:28.541 --> 01:57:30.457
[breathing shakily]

2164
01:57:31.291 --> 01:57:32.500
For the guilty.

2165
01:57:33.082 --> 01:57:34.166
[Martha] Mr. Blanc.

2166
01:57:34.832 --> 01:57:36.457
You know the truth.

2167
01:57:37.041 --> 01:57:39.041
I do. yes.

2168
01:57:40.582 --> 01:57:43.914
And you made yourself the fool just now.

2169
01:57:43.916 --> 01:57:46.625
So that you could do this
of your own free will.

2170
01:57:47.916 --> 01:57:50.414
And now you better do it. Quickly.

2171
01:57:50.416 --> 01:57:51.707
Thank you.

2172
01:57:55.582 --> 01:57:57.000
Father Jud.

2173
01:57:57.500 --> 01:57:59.500
[breathing shakily]

2174
01:58:04.000 --> 01:58:05.123
[softly] What do I do?

2175
01:58:05.125 --> 01:58:07.039
What you were born to do.

2176
01:58:07.041 --> 01:58:08.541
Be her priest.

2177
01:58:09.041 --> 01:58:10.457
Take her confession.

2178
01:58:19.125 --> 01:58:21.123
Bless me. Father. for I have sinned.

2179
01:58:21.125 --> 01:58:23.416
It is a week since my last confession.

2180
01:58:27.916 --> 01:58:32.750
I told myself it started with pure intent.

2181
01:58:34.125 --> 01:58:35.541
But the truth is

2182
01:58:36.375 --> 01:58:39.457
it started with a lie.

2183
01:58:40.416 --> 01:58:41.498
Prentice.

2184
01:58:41.500 --> 01:58:42.957
[intriguing string music plays]

2185
01:58:42.957 --> 01:58:43.957
[Martha] <i>Prentice.</i>

2186
01:58:45.625 --> 01:58:48.625
<i>I saw him take his final communion.</i>

2187
01:58:52.500 --> 01:58:54.625
This is Eve's Apple. Martha.

2188
01:58:55.207 --> 01:58:57.416
My entire cursed fortune.

2189
01:58:57.916 --> 01:59:00.332
All the sin in the world.

2190
01:59:00.332 --> 01:59:02.332
All that Eve hungers for.

2191
01:59:03.000 --> 01:59:04.625
I have trapped it.

2192
01:59:05.207 --> 01:59:08.625
It shall never again
be plucked by evil hands.

2193
01:59:09.416 --> 01:59:11.332
The body of Christ.

2194
01:59:12.707 --> 01:59:14.123
[music turns ominous]

2195
01:59:14.125 --> 01:59:15.250
[groaning]

2196
01:59:16.375 --> 01:59:17.832
[Prentice gulps. groans]

2197
01:59:19.916 --> 01:59:21.457
[exhales]

2198
01:59:24.457 --> 01:59:27.873
[Martha] <i>He took the jewel to his grave.</i>

2199
01:59:27.875 --> 01:59:29.957
[suspenseful music plays]

2200
01:59:30.625 --> 01:59:35.291
<i>I swore that I would
protect this great secret.</i>

2201
01:59:36.707 --> 01:59:40.623
<i>But Grace. she discovered that
he had bought the diamond.</i>

2202
01:59:40.625 --> 01:59:41.998
I don't know how.

2203
01:59:42.000 --> 01:59:43.916
She knew her fancy brands.

2204
01:59:45.166 --> 01:59:48.498
<i>What would come
in a custom-made FabergÃ© box.</i>

2205
01:59:48.500 --> 01:59:50.748
<i>itself worth maybe $20.000?</i>

2206
01:59:50.750 --> 01:59:54.914
<i>Not a trinket or a plastic Jesus. no.</i>

2207
01:59:54.916 --> 01:59:57.166
<i>Something facet-cut. worth a fortune.</i>

2208
01:59:58.250 --> 01:59:59.332
<i>A jewel.</i>

2209
01:59:59.332 --> 02:00:02.123
But she didn't know where he hid it.

2210
02:00:02.125 --> 02:00:03.707
So that night...

2211
02:00:06.166 --> 02:00:08.291
<i>She didn't desecrate the church in anger.</i>

2212
02:00:08.875 --> 02:00:11.914
[Benoit] <i>No. she was looking for
the hidden jewel.</i>

2213
02:00:11.916 --> 02:00:15.500
- [Grace sobbing]
- [Benoit] <i>A dark life of desperation.</i>

2214
02:00:16.041 --> 02:00:19.125
<i>A prisoner to shame and judgment.</i>

2215
02:00:19.625 --> 02:00:21.625
<i>It was her one way out.</i>

2216
02:00:22.625 --> 02:00:24.041
That poor girl.

2217
02:00:25.582 --> 02:00:27.416
Martha. what did you say to her?

2218
02:00:29.541 --> 02:00:31.373
I know where he hid it.

2219
02:00:31.375 --> 02:00:33.498
And you'll never find it.

2220
02:00:33.500 --> 02:00:35.000
You harlot whore.

2221
02:00:40.207 --> 02:00:42.123
- [yells] Where is it?
- [screams]

2222
02:00:42.125 --> 02:00:44.748
- [yelling]
- [giggling]

2223
02:00:44.750 --> 02:00:47.207
Where is it. you little shit?

2224
02:00:48.207 --> 02:00:51.289
I kept the secret of Eve's Apple

2225
02:00:51.291 --> 02:00:55.957
locked in my heart for 60 years.

2226
02:00:57.125 --> 02:00:59.750
My terrible burden.

2227
02:01:00.957 --> 02:01:03.164
Until...

2228
02:01:03.166 --> 02:01:05.082
[melancholic music plays]

2229
02:01:05.082 --> 02:01:07.248
I challenged you to confess it.

2230
02:01:07.250 --> 02:01:10.707
- [imperceptible]
- [Martha] <i>With defiant pride.</i>

2231
02:01:11.750 --> 02:01:13.166
<i>I confessed.</i>

2232
02:01:14.000 --> 02:01:16.166
[panting]

2233
02:01:16.750 --> 02:01:18.375
To the wrong priest.

2234
02:01:19.916 --> 02:01:21.250
[breath trembles]

2235
02:01:22.582 --> 02:01:24.623
Time is of the essence now.

2236
02:01:24.625 --> 02:01:26.707
Last Sunday. in the rectory.

2237
02:01:26.707 --> 02:01:29.957
<i>Vera confronted Wicks
and you learned about Cy.</i>

2238
02:01:29.957 --> 02:01:32.998
I could accept that he had strayed.

2239
02:01:33.000 --> 02:01:36.791
- [imperceptible]
<i>- But as he spoke. something became clear.</i>

2240
02:01:37.707 --> 02:01:39.916
<i>This was something much bigger.</i>

2241
02:01:40.416 --> 02:01:44.832
<i>He was embracing that terrible boy.</i>

2242
02:01:46.541 --> 02:01:48.664
<i>That's when I suspected.</i>

2243
02:01:48.666 --> 02:01:51.123
So you call the construction company.

2244
02:01:51.125 --> 02:01:52.625
Thank you. James.

2245
02:01:54.875 --> 02:01:56.082
[Martha] <i>And I was certain.</i>

2246
02:01:57.000 --> 02:02:00.414
<i>He had ordered the equipment
to open the crypt</i>

2247
02:02:00.416 --> 02:02:06.332
<i>to steal the diamond
for his own greed and lust for power.</i>

2248
02:02:06.332 --> 02:02:10.875
<i>The corrupting sin
of Eve's Apple would be unearthed</i>

2249
02:02:11.541 --> 02:02:13.957
<i>and this church would fall</i>

2250
02:02:13.957 --> 02:02:18.664
<i>because of everything
Prentice had warned me about.</i>

2251
02:02:18.666 --> 02:02:20.166
<i>I had failed him.</i>

2252
02:02:22.750 --> 02:02:23.957
All my life.

2253
02:02:24.582 --> 02:02:27.916
I was not the bad one. I was the good one.

2254
02:02:28.500 --> 02:02:30.082
The faithful one.

2255
02:02:30.082 --> 02:02:32.791
Serving and protecting the church.

2256
02:02:33.416 --> 02:02:36.498
If I failed in that. what is my life?

2257
02:02:36.500 --> 02:02:37.664
I understand.

2258
02:02:37.666 --> 02:02:40.373
My sole purpose

2259
02:02:40.375 --> 02:02:41.875
and I failed.

2260
02:02:42.957 --> 02:02:44.166
Unless...

2261
02:02:45.375 --> 02:02:46.750
[breath trembles]

2262
02:02:48.166 --> 02:02:49.125
Unless...

2263
02:02:51.832 --> 02:02:55.582
<i>Unless I could...
I could steal the jewel first</i>

2264
02:02:55.582 --> 02:02:57.416
<i>and get rid of it forever.</i>

2265
02:02:58.416 --> 02:02:59.832
<i>And with the same stroke.</i>

2266
02:02:59.832 --> 02:03:04.164
<i>raise Wicks up
as a miraculous risen saint.</i>

2267
02:03:04.166 --> 02:03:07.666
<i>Not a fallible man. but a symbol</i>

2268
02:03:08.500 --> 02:03:10.500
<i>that would save my church.</i>

2269
02:03:11.666 --> 02:03:14.207
<i>All it would take is a miracle.</i>

2270
02:03:15.582 --> 02:03:17.416
So I formed my plan.

2271
02:03:18.416 --> 02:03:22.500
Wicks' death must be a holy mystery.

2272
02:03:23.291 --> 02:03:26.375
Unsolvable and divine.

2273
02:03:27.375 --> 02:03:29.125
But you couldn't do it alone.

2274
02:03:29.832 --> 02:03:30.916
No.

2275
02:03:32.457 --> 02:03:34.082
<i>A weak man. I thought.</i>

2276
02:03:34.666 --> 02:03:35.873
<i>Desperate.</i>

2277
02:03:35.875 --> 02:03:38.707
<i>Someone who would fall in line
to save the church</i>

2278
02:03:38.707 --> 02:03:41.375
<i>and stay in line to cover his shame.</i>

2279
02:03:41.957 --> 02:03:45.914
And who had access
to medical-grade tranquilizers.

2280
02:03:45.916 --> 02:03:48.041
Yes. And that.

2281
02:03:51.457 --> 02:03:54.416
<i>It all went according to plan.</i>

2282
02:03:56.000 --> 02:03:58.082
<i>Oh. God.</i> [breathing heavily]

2283
02:03:58.082 --> 02:03:59.248
<i>My vanity.</i>

2284
02:03:59.250 --> 02:04:00.750
So wicked.

2285
02:04:01.291 --> 02:04:02.416
[Jud] Martha.

2286
02:04:03.041 --> 02:04:05.500
I understand. I promise. I do.

2287
02:04:06.082 --> 02:04:07.914
Keep going. I'm here.

2288
02:04:07.916 --> 02:04:10.375
[Martha] I didn't reckon the cost.

2289
02:04:11.457 --> 02:04:13.291
Forgive me. Samson.

2290
02:04:13.832 --> 02:04:16.248
Strong Samson. faithful Samson.

2291
02:04:16.250 --> 02:04:18.875
Samson. Who made the coffins.

2292
02:04:21.541 --> 02:04:23.832
[grunts] Shit.

2293
02:04:24.625 --> 02:04:26.041
[Martha] You will rise again.

2294
02:04:27.000 --> 02:04:28.832
It will be okay.

2295
02:04:28.832 --> 02:04:30.541
You will rise again.

2296
02:04:31.125 --> 02:04:33.373
It will be okay. [exhales]

2297
02:04:33.375 --> 02:04:35.332
[melancholic music plays]

2298
02:04:35.332 --> 02:04:36.625
I promise.

2299
02:04:37.332 --> 02:04:40.539
<i>He didn't understand why we were doing it.</i>

2300
02:04:40.541 --> 02:04:43.457
Anything for you. my angel.

2301
02:04:44.207 --> 02:04:45.375
[Martha] <i>But he trusted me.</i>

2302
02:04:45.875 --> 02:04:47.707
<i>Because he loved me.</i>

2303
02:04:48.375 --> 02:04:50.500
Oh. Lord. [sobs]

2304
02:04:55.250 --> 02:04:57.082
How did it go so wrong?

2305
02:04:57.666 --> 02:04:59.664
[thunder crashing]

2306
02:04:59.666 --> 02:05:01.748
[Martha] <i>It was supposed to be so simple.</i>

2307
02:05:01.750 --> 02:05:03.789
<i>The doctor gives the signal.</i>

2308
02:05:03.791 --> 02:05:05.000
[cell phone chimes]

2309
02:05:16.207 --> 02:05:18.625
[Martha] <i>Samson retrieves the jewel.</i>

2310
02:05:19.875 --> 02:05:22.707
<i>The Lazarus door serves its purpose.</i>

2311
02:05:25.541 --> 02:05:26.789
[beeps]

2312
02:05:26.791 --> 02:05:30.166
<i>All caught on camera the way we planned.</i>

2313
02:05:30.791 --> 02:05:33.582
<i>Dr. Nat would drive off
with Wicks' body in his truck</i>

2314
02:05:34.500 --> 02:05:37.832
<i>and dispose of it
in that nasty gook in his cellar.</i>

2315
02:05:37.832 --> 02:05:41.998
<i>And the next day. Samson would
tell the tale of the risen saint</i>

2316
02:05:42.000 --> 02:05:46.082
<i>and his word of blessing
to his faithful groundskeeper</i>

2317
02:05:46.082 --> 02:05:49.000
<i>before ascending back into heaven.</i>

2318
02:05:49.666 --> 02:05:51.082
<i>A miracle.</i>

2319
02:05:51.666 --> 02:05:53.500
<i>It would have been perfect.</i>

2320
02:05:55.416 --> 02:05:57.539
I wasn't supposed to be there.

2321
02:05:57.541 --> 02:05:59.666
You most certainly were not.

2322
02:06:00.457 --> 02:06:01.539
[Benoit] Did you know

2323
02:06:01.541 --> 02:06:04.707
what had happened
when you found Samson's body?

2324
02:06:04.707 --> 02:06:06.498
I had an idea.

2325
02:06:06.500 --> 02:06:08.582
[sobbing] No. no!

2326
02:06:09.250 --> 02:06:11.082
But I had to be sure.

2327
02:06:14.541 --> 02:06:15.750
[Nat] Praise be.

2328
02:06:16.250 --> 02:06:17.457
It's accomplished.

2329
02:06:35.957 --> 02:06:39.291
- [clatters]
- Oh. Oh. Oh.

2330
02:06:42.207 --> 02:06:44.207
[Martha] <i>Then he told me the fairy tale</i>

2331
02:06:44.207 --> 02:06:47.291
<i>of how everything
had gone according to plan.</i>

2332
02:06:48.750 --> 02:06:52.207
<i>It was only then that I told him
I'd been to the crypt.</i>

2333
02:06:54.000 --> 02:06:56.666
<i>- And I knew he was lying.</i>
- [gulps]

2334
02:06:58.416 --> 02:07:00.541
[Martha] <i>And then he told me the truth.</i>

2335
02:07:01.500 --> 02:07:03.250
- [thunder rumbling]
- [yelps. groans]

2336
02:07:05.332 --> 02:07:07.750
Shit. We can't let him see us.

2337
02:07:08.791 --> 02:07:10.375
[Jud pants. groans]

2338
02:07:12.250 --> 02:07:13.457
[gasps softly]

2339
02:07:16.332 --> 02:07:17.541
[Nat] Jesus.

2340
02:07:20.541 --> 02:07:22.166
[Martha] <i>My second mistake.</i>

2341
02:07:22.666 --> 02:07:27.291
<i>Underestimating the temptation
of Eve's Apple.</i>

2342
02:07:28.541 --> 02:07:32.998
<i>Our agreed mission was to destroy it
or throw it in the sea.</i>

2343
02:07:33.000 --> 02:07:37.500
<i>But all this power will I give thee.</i>

2344
02:07:38.416 --> 02:07:41.539
<i>Christ himself could resist temptation.</i>

2345
02:07:41.541 --> 02:07:44.832
<i>but this desperate little man.</i>

2346
02:07:45.332 --> 02:07:48.541
<i>all that stood in his way
was Samson and I.</i>

2347
02:07:49.375 --> 02:07:51.375
<i>Now. here was his opportunity.</i>

2348
02:07:52.250 --> 02:07:55.498
To remove his obstacles.

2349
02:07:55.500 --> 02:07:56.498
[thunder crashes]

2350
02:07:56.500 --> 02:08:00.582
Frame a young priest with a violent past

2351
02:08:00.582 --> 02:08:02.500
and keep the jewel.

2352
02:08:04.457 --> 02:08:05.289
He took it.

2353
02:08:05.291 --> 02:08:06.707
[yells]

2354
02:08:09.832 --> 02:08:13.789
<i>Then all that remained in his way was me.</i>

2355
02:08:13.791 --> 02:08:14.707
[imperceptible]

2356
02:08:14.707 --> 02:08:19.291
<i>He had poisoned my coffee
with a lethal dose of pentobarbital.</i>

2357
02:08:20.207 --> 02:08:22.832
<i>No remedy once ingested.</i>

2358
02:08:23.582 --> 02:08:24.914
<i>Mm. painless.</i>

2359
02:08:24.916 --> 02:08:27.832
<i>A little numbness in the lips.</i>

2360
02:08:28.500 --> 02:08:31.582
<i>Then in ten minutes.
time for your final prayer.</i>

2361
02:08:32.416 --> 02:08:35.664
<i>Then he begged me to understand
why he was doing all this.</i>

2362
02:08:35.666 --> 02:08:39.207
<i>That the money would lure back
his harpy wife.</i>

2363
02:08:39.207 --> 02:08:41.125
<i>blah. blah. blah.</i>

2364
02:08:41.832 --> 02:08:44.082
<i>I told him I understood.</i>

2365
02:08:45.416 --> 02:08:47.416
<i>I understood why he did it.</i>

2366
02:08:48.707 --> 02:08:49.791
- [clatters]
- Oh.

2367
02:08:51.875 --> 02:08:54.500
[Martha] <i>I had understood it all.</i>

2368
02:09:14.707 --> 02:09:16.707
[Martha] <i>These things I did with</i>

2369
02:09:17.457 --> 02:09:20.082
<i>hatred in my heart.</i>

2370
02:09:25.166 --> 02:09:27.582
[Martha] <i>Vengeance is mine. said the Lord.</i>

2371
02:09:33.125 --> 02:09:36.625
<i>And that is the story
the crime scene will tell the world. but...</i>

2372
02:09:37.207 --> 02:09:39.498
- [squeaks]
- [liquid sloshing]

2373
02:09:39.500 --> 02:09:41.416
[Martha] <i>...inside my heart.</i>

2374
02:09:42.166 --> 02:09:43.375
<i>I know.</i>

2375
02:09:44.375 --> 02:09:45.332
[switch clicks]

2376
02:09:47.457 --> 02:09:49.082
Vengeance is mine.

2377
02:09:52.916 --> 02:09:56.498
These sins I confess to you. Father.

2378
02:09:56.500 --> 02:09:59.791
[breathing heavily] I have lied.
I have killed.

2379
02:10:00.500 --> 02:10:01.707
and now

2380
02:10:02.707 --> 02:10:05.332
I have topped it all off
with a real doozy.

2381
02:10:05.332 --> 02:10:07.541
[breathing heavily]

2382
02:10:09.957 --> 02:10:11.207
[gasps]

2383
02:10:13.000 --> 02:10:14.623
Father. Quickly now. quickly.

2384
02:10:14.625 --> 02:10:15.998
[hesitates] What's happening?

2385
02:10:16.000 --> 02:10:18.125
I knew when I saw her lips...

2386
02:10:20.166 --> 02:10:21.873
<i>it was already too late.</i>

2387
02:10:21.875 --> 02:10:22.875
[sighs]

2388
02:10:23.707 --> 02:10:25.707
She's taken the pentobarbital.

2389
02:10:25.707 --> 02:10:28.707
- Oh. Oh. God. Call the ambulance now!
- On it!

2390
02:10:28.707 --> 02:10:31.207
There might be a poison kit
in the prowler!

2391
02:10:38.750 --> 02:10:40.916
[labored breathing]

2392
02:10:42.707 --> 02:10:44.332
Forgive me. Father.

2393
02:10:45.541 --> 02:10:46.957
for all you have endured.

2394
02:10:48.625 --> 02:10:53.457
Forgive me. Lord. for...
for Wicks and Nat and...

2395
02:10:55.666 --> 02:10:56.875
Samson.

2396
02:10:57.500 --> 02:10:59.125
[sobs] My sweet Samson.

2397
02:11:00.207 --> 02:11:01.416
And Grace.

2398
02:11:06.000 --> 02:11:08.082
- [huffs]
- [Jud] Martha.

2399
02:11:08.832 --> 02:11:10.041
Grace.

2400
02:11:12.625 --> 02:11:13.832
You're safe now.

2401
02:11:16.666 --> 02:11:17.875
Let it go.

2402
02:11:19.457 --> 02:11:21.082
Let the hatred go.

2403
02:11:26.457 --> 02:11:27.541
Grace.

2404
02:11:31.207 --> 02:11:32.332
Yes.

2405
02:11:33.207 --> 02:11:34.625
I see it now.

2406
02:11:36.541 --> 02:11:38.166
That poor girl.

2407
02:11:41.332 --> 02:11:43.166
Forgive me. Grace.

2408
02:11:47.375 --> 02:11:48.582
Father...

2409
02:11:51.582 --> 02:11:53.207
you're really good at this.

2410
02:11:53.207 --> 02:11:54.291
[chuckles]

2411
02:11:58.707 --> 02:12:00.875
God. the father of mercies.

2412
02:12:01.625 --> 02:12:04.123
through the death
and resurrection of His Son

2413
02:12:04.125 --> 02:12:06.832
has reconciled the world to Himself

2414
02:12:07.582 --> 02:12:11.750
and poured out the Holy Spirit
for the forgiveness of sins.

2415
02:12:12.582 --> 02:12:14.498
and through the ministry of the Church.

2416
02:12:14.500 --> 02:12:17.000
may God grant you pardon and peace.

2417
02:12:18.000 --> 02:12:20.207
and I absolve you of your sins.

2418
02:12:28.000 --> 02:12:31.207
In the name of the Father and of the Son

2419
02:12:32.291 --> 02:12:33.707
and the Holy Spirit.

2420
02:12:46.166 --> 02:12:47.666
[clangs]

2421
02:12:49.416 --> 02:12:50.500
Shit.

2422
02:13:11.332 --> 02:13:13.125
[Jud breathing heavily]

2423
02:13:15.875 --> 02:13:17.875
